title: banana split ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into freezer container.
Add milk if needed to fill.
Freeze!
(We put in blender.)

title: play dough
directions: Mix together in a pan.
Heat slowly until mixture lumps together.
Remove from heat.
Stir with hands or spoon until play dough consistency.
Knead a few times.
Store in a tightly closed container.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter and jelly onto the bread, then put the two slices of bread together.
Repeat until full.

title: chicken salad
directions: Stew chicken breasts with 2 stalks celery and salt.
Throw away celery stalks when chicken is done.
Mix with remaining ingredients and serve.

title: chicken salad with twist
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions. Drain and cool. Combine next 6 ingredients and stir until blended.
Add to macaroni, stirring well.
Stir in chicken, cucumber, celery, olives and onion.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve in lettuce lined dish.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix oil, sugars, vanilla, eggs and bananas. Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to liquid and mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into 5 or 6 loaf pans.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: light and luscious microwave summer squash(very low in calories)
directions: Dice squash into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add chopped onion, salt and pepper and mix together.
Place covered casserole in microwave.
Cook on High for 12 to 16 minutes (depending on how soft you like your squash).
Let sit, covered, for 6 to 8 minutes. Serves 4.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in 8 x 8-inch cake pan or small casserole. Don't stir.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and margarine in double boiler.
While cooling, mix the rest of the ingredients.
Add to the candy bar mixture.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese stuffed vegetables
directions: In medium bowl with mixer at low speed, beat soup and cream cheese until well blended.
Beat in lemon juice, garlic, savory and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: blender coconut creme pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender. Pour into a 10-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, heat soup, sour cream, cheese, cheese mix, margarine and milk.
Add potatoes.
Pour into 3-quart oblong pan.
Top with extra cheese and buttered cracker crumbs. Casserole can be refrigerated for 1 hour.
I have used regular potatoes in this recipe.
Boil 12 potatoes whole for 25 minutes. Remove skins and dice up.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain kidney beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Goes well on picnics or barbecue.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Pack the apples and white sugar in greased pan (2 inches deep).
Blend the brown sugar, butter and flour.
Spread over apples and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes.
Beat eggs, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Heat oil in skillet.
Dip tomatoes in egg mixture, then into breading, then place into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Delicious at breakfast or any time!

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar in top of double boiler or in microwave (low power).
Mix chocolate in 2/3 of Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Ice with remaining Cool Whip.
Grate remaining chocolate bar on top. Refrigerate 1 hour or more.
Can be done day before.

title: cracker candy
directions: Layer saltines on an aluminum foil-lined jelly roll pan. Bring butter and sugar to boil over medium heat.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour and spread mixture over saltines.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly and sprinkle with chocolate chips, spreading as they melt.
Top with nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: tammy's rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over Crisco, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add egg yeast to Crisco mixture.
Add flour to make soft dough.
Rub with Crisco and let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Punch down and make rolls.
Let rise again in warm place and bake at 425°.

title: individual quiches(creamy, easy to hold seafood pies)
directions: On floured surface, roll half of pastry into 12-inch circle. Cut six 4-inch circles.
Repeat with remaining pastry.
Fit into twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Fill each with some shrimp, onion and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients.
Pour over cheese. Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes 12.

title: hot pepper dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill before serving with crackers.

title: franklin pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add 3 cups flour that has been sifted with baking powder and salt.
Mix remaining flour with cherries, pineapple and chopped pecans.
Stir into batter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake in a very slow oven at 250° for 3 hours.
Allow to cool in pan.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Remove.
Add onion, pepper and celery. Saute until just wilted.
Add soups and water.
Return chops to skillet.
Add mushrooms.
Stir and mix well.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: spaghetti with tomato sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add oil; turn heat to medium.
Stir in onions and cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste; stir in oregano, sugar, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cover saucepan.
Cook gently on low heat for 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
(The longer the sauce cooks, the better the flavor.)
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Stir sauce into spaghetti and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Grease a spring-form cake pan. Preheat oven to 350°. Place all ingredients in a blender on high until blended well.
Pour batter into pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°. When cool, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins until done.
Drain off and save juice.
Cool. Mix shortening and sugar, salt and eggs together.
Mix raisin juice and soda together and add to first mixture.
Add raisins, flour, cinnamon, nuts and oats.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet and bake at 375°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut surprises
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Shape dough around pieces of fruit.
Roll in coconut and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt together in a saucepan oleo and chocolate.
Cool.
Add sugar, salt, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a greased pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
(I think it is best when still warm.)

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimientos, pepper and 1/2 cup of the crumbs.
Pour into a shallow casserole; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Save broth.
Mix soups and chicken broth (from cooked chicken) and heat until lumps are gone.
Mix chicken Stove Top dressing and seasoning with melted margarine.
Put 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of large baking dish. Tear boiled chicken in pieces and put on top of stuffing.
Pour soup mix over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining Stove Top dressing on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy cheese cakes
directions: Blend
first
ingredients.
Place wafers in aluminum foil cups.
Bake
10 minutes at 375°; cool.
Add pie filling. Paper baking cups may be used.

title: ambrosia
directions: Cut oranges into slices.
Peel and cut into quarters.
Add pineapple, coconut, marshmallows and salad dressing.
Mix, refrigerate and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: norwegian brown beans
directions: Mix ground beef, onions and salt.
Roll meat into small balls; fry in oil until brown.
Add to meat the catsup, water, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
In large casserole dish, place both beans and pineapple.
Add meatballs and 1/2 cup of pineapple.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: charlene's potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix everything together except the corn flakes and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 3 tablespoons melted butter and crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mash sweet potatoes.
Add eggs, orange juice, butter, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Transfer to a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Top with marshmallows; return to oven until they begin to puff and melt, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: crabmeat imperial
directions: Beat eggs; mix in other ingredients, then fold (do not crease) in crabmeat.
Sprinkle top with bread.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Toss stuffing mix with margarine in a bowl. Combine squash, onions, soup and sour cream in a bowl; mix well. Spread 1/4 of the stuffing mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer with squash mixture and remaining stuffing mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until brown and bubbly. Makes 10 servings.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix milk with pudding.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over Jell-O.

title: spiced mixed nuts
directions: Combine
egg
white and water.	Add nuts; toss to coat. Combine
sugar, pumpkin pie spice and salt.
Add to nuts; toss until
all	are well coated.
Place in single layer on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool nuts
on
waxed
paper.
Break up large clusters.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: it's a snap cheese cake
directions: In large bowl, mix Knox gelatine and sugar; add water and stir well.
With electric mixer, beat in cream cheese until smooth. Pour into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours, then serve.

title: creamy salsa dip
directions: Heat cream cheese and salsa in 1-quart saucepan over low heat about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cream cheese is melted.
Keep warm.
Serve with snacks.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups dip.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in large pot.
Retain broth.
Pick chicken from bones.
Bring broth to boil.
Stretch each biscuit and tear into 3 or 4 pieces; drop into broth.
Add chicken; stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Cover and cook until dumplings are done. Season to taste.
Serves 4 to 6, depending on size of chicken.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a trifle bowl.
Very colorful and refreshing!

title: baked zucchini
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: potatoes
directions: Mix together and put bread crumbs on top.
Bake covered one hour at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in blended flour, salt and pepper (reserve leftover flour mixture).
Brown meat well in the butter, sprinkle with garlic salt.
Then add onions and mushrooms and cook until tender.
Sprinkle reserved flour mixture over meat and stir. Gradually add bouillon, stirring until bubbly and thickened.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, catsup and sour cream.
Heat well.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: german potato salad
directions: *Three-quart pot makes enough to take to a potluck dinner; recipe may be reduced for a family dinner.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail, 1 cup coconut and eggs; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 cake pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil in small saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes. Stir in remaining coconut.
Pour over hot cake while still in pan.

title: pineapple delight salad
directions: Mix jello, water, marshmallows and cream cheese.
Add pineapple, pecans and mayonnaise.
Stir in whipped cream and let set.

title: shrimp pie
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, garlic and celery in margarine.
Cut shrimp and add to listed ingredients.
Cook until shrimp are pink. Add flour, mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Pour in crust, cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: danny's dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and Velveeta cheese in either microwave or on top of stove.
Add chili, green chilies and chili powder.
Heat and serve with tostados.

title: george's favorite breakfast
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces in iron skillet and make a place in center of skillet for hash browns.
Cook until done over medium heat, about 15 minutes. Beat the eggs and pour over the bacon potato mixture. Turn once and cut in half.

title: brownie stew(good for cooking on camp fire)
directions: In a large skillet, melt bacon grease.
Dice onion and brown in bacon grease with ground beef.
Add chili powder and brown sugar.
Stir well.
Add pork and beans.
Cook down well.
Serve with fried potatoes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle top with almonds (small amount).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.

title: zucchini stuffing
directions: Beat eggs; add zucchini, bread crumbs, milk, cheese and onion. Put in greased casserole and pour melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kay's ginger rice
directions: To the pot, add oil and chopped onion.
Brown onion, then add rice, cold water, bouillon cubes and bay leaf.
Cover pot and cook on low for 30 minutes without lifting the pot top.
Before serving, add toasted almonds across top and sprinkle with ginger.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and remove from bone.
Layer in casserole dish.
Add drained green beans.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together until smooth.
May need to add small amount of water.
Pour over green beans.
Add enough cheese to cover your last layer well.
Add cracker crumbs.
Drizzle butter over top. Put in oven and bake until cheese is melted and other ingredients are hot.

title: pepper cabbage(old dutch recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: homemade chili
directions: Put chili powder seasoning in the ground beef.
Brown the ground beef and then pour it into a larger pan.
After all the seasonings are put into the larger pot, let it simmer for 60 minutes or 1 hour.
Stir often!

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until tender.
Remove from broth.
Strain broth, reserving 2 2/3 cups.
Bone chicken and chop into small pieces; set aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Great served with strawberries, honeydew melons or cantaloupe.

title: vegetable relish dish
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine onion, cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour margarine over chicken. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam peppers for 5 minutes in boiling water.
Mix meat and rice together. Stuff mixture in peppers. Place in baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes, covered, then remove lid.
Pour about 4 ounces of tomato sauce over peppers and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: batter for onion rings or cauliflower
directions: Beat until smooth.
Dip into mixture and drop in hot Crisco oil.

title: tater tot-vegetable hot dish
directions: Press ground beef raw in cake pan (8 x 8-inches).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain most of juice off can of vegetables and put over meat.
Pour cream soup over.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 400° or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Whip eggs and sugar in bowl.
Add sweet potatoes, salt and allspice and beat again.
Stir in lemon juice, milk and chopped pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes, then change temperature to 325° and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: best ever lemonade
directions: Peel lemons and put rinds into a bowl. Cover with sugar and let stand a half hour. Boil water; pour over lemons and sugar. When cool, take out rinds. Squeeze lemons; strain and add to sugar mixture. Chill and serve ice cold.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and margarine.
Beat until almost stiff.
Put in buttered dish, cool, cut and enjoy.

title: cheese and spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased, shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: spinach-cheese manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well and squeeze dry; set aside.
Place 1 cup of spaghetti sauce in bottom of dish.
Stir in water; set aside.
In medium bowl, beat egg. Stir in Ricotta, 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese, spinach, salt and pepper; blend well.
Using a table knife, fill uncooked manicotti shells with spinach mixture.
Arrange in dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells to coat completely.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake 1 1/4 hours or until shells are very tender.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 7 servings.

title: chicken, rice, broccoli and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rancho california rice
directions: In large skillet saute onions in butter.
Add rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Mix together.
In a greased casserole put a layer of rice, then a layer of canned green chilies (unseeded and cut in strips) and 1/2 cup grated cheese, alternately (use total of 1 1/2 cups cheese in layers).
Repeat ending with layer of rice.
Bake for 25 minutes in 375° oven. Remove, sprinkle remaining cheese over top and return to bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in baking dish.
Mix topping and spread on top.

title: white bread
directions: Mixing:
Combine the water, milk and oil in a saucepan and heat until lukewarm.
Pour into mixing bowl and add honey or sugar, yeast, 2 cups flour, then salt.
Beat the mixture for 2 minutes by hand or electric mixer.
Stirring with a large spoon, gradually add flour until the dough pulls away cleanly from sides of the bowl.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Mix in peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until it starts to stiffen.
Pour into greased pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in oblong dish (10 x 6-inch).
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients together, then combine with egg, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Cover with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until crusty and brown.

title: leann's breakfast surprise
directions: Fry bacon and remove from skillet.
Add potatoes and onions to bacon grease.
Add eggs that have been slightly beaten and cover with grated cheese.
Cook over slow heat until potatoes are tender.
Do not stir.
After completely cooked, top with crumbled bacon and serve in skillet.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Boil the eggs.
Tear up leaf lettuce into serving bowl. Sprinkle with chopped green onion tops and chopped egg.
Heat the fat.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat liquid thoroughly.
Pour over lettuce mixture.
Toss and serve at once.

title: play doh
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over ingredients and mix well.
Food coloring may be added.
Store in Ziploc bag or airtight container.

title: larapin good dip
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: company cheese strata
directions: Cut bread slices with 2 3/4-inch doughnut cutter to make 12 rounds; tear remaining bread portions into 1-inch pieces and arrange in bottom of greased medium roasting pan.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese, ham, Parmesan and green onion over bread pieces. Arrange bread rounds over cheese-ham layer.
In large Mix-N-Store pitcher combine remaining 4 ingredients; pour over bread and cheese layers.
Seal and chill at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: mushroom pork chops
directions: Coat the pork chops lightly in flour and brown in a frying pan.
Put in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix the peas, soup, milk and 1/2 cup of water.
Pour over the pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve over mashed potatoes. Serves 6.

title: "hanky-panky"
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in large skillet; drain well. Return to skillet; add Velveeta chunks.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Place rye slices on cookie sheet.
Top with cheese mixture.
Place under broiler until cheese is golden brown.

title: cheese-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery, bell peppers and garlic until soft.
Add Vegeburger and continue sauteing for 20 more minutes.
Add soup, water and seasoning.
Combine tomato sauce and cottage cheese together in separate bowl.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a blender.
Add pineapple juice.
Pour in a gallon jug and freeze.
Take out of freezer 2 or 3 hours before serving.
Pour ginger ale over frozen mold.
Makes a slushy punch.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk, sugar, salt and shortening mixture.
Allow to cool until lukewarm.
In separate bowl mix yeast with about 1 teaspoon of sugar and 1/4 cup warm water; let dissolve.
Pour yeast mixture into lukewarm milk.
Add 1 cup water and eggs; beat well, then add flour while mixing.
Pour mixture in a greased bowl and cover with damp cloth.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight or until you are ready to cook.
Roll out and cut biscuit size.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Combine with rice, onions, soup, corn and Cheez Whiz in casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes or until edges are browned.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar and syrup in a glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Stir in margarine and vanilla; cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Quickly stir in soda; spread on buttered cookie sheet and let cool.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Cook at 400° until brown on top.

title: sausage dip
directions: Lightly brown and scramble meat together.
Drain.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Serve warm with chips.

title: dump cake
directions: In an ungreased 13 x 9-inch roasting pan, spread pie filling. Layer pineapple over pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all. Dot with thin pats of butter or oleo.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook onions, broccoli and red pepper in oil until tender.
Add undiluted soups, water, milk and peas.
Cook until peas are tender.
Simmer 10 more minutes and add grated cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: stir and drop chocolate cookies
directions: Beat eggs with fork until well blended.
Stir in Wesson oil and vanilla.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add to egg mixture.
Add melted, cooled chocolate and nuts.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together for 2 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Blend well and pour into a shallow greased pan about 10 x 8-inch.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for approximately 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while still warm and roll in powdered sugar.

title: panocha candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter and milk.
Cook, stirring only until sugar dissolves to soft ball stage.
Cool at room temperature without stirring until lukewarm.
Add vanilla. Beat mixture until it holds its shape.
Add nuts, quickly spread in greased pan.
Cool and cut in squares.
Makes 2 dozen pieces.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Spread bread with cream cheese.
Slice in strips.
Roll up with cream cheese on the inside.
Wrap 1 slice of bacon around bread/cheese roll.
Anchor with toothpick.
Broil until crisp. Best served warm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll out on floured board and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Fill buttered pie plate 2/3 full with sliced apples. Sprinkle on top 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Mix together in bowl the sugar, flour, egg, melted margarine, salt and nuts. Spoon this mixture on top of apples. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini italiano
directions: Wash zucchini, slice thin.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Add onion; saute until golden.
Add zucchini, sprinkle with salt. Toss.
Cover.
Braise about 5 minutes or until crisp-tender. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: taco cheese meat loaf
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Top with reserved cheese.
Serves 8.

title: grilled roast marinade
directions: This will marinate a 3 to 5 pound roast.
Pierce roast and rub in meat tenderizer.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over roast.
Place in an airtight container for 24 hours.
Grill for 20 minutes for medium rare or longer for medium to well done.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Press into patties.
Cook on grill or in skillet.
Sprinkle onion salt on top of burgers. (Reduces fat from regular ground beef by 50%.)

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix vinegar, soup, sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and oil in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Allow to refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.
Will keep in refrigerator for about 2 weeks.

title: better-than-sex cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl by hand.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Needs no icing.

title: pastelli(italian soup)
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Mix well and press through a potato ricer into boiling chicken broth.
Simmer 20 minutes.
May be served with additional grated cheese.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine crabmeat, cream cheese, onion and grated Parmesan cheese.
Add rest of ingredients to taste.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into marble-size balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Alternate layers of ingredients except white sauce in casserole dish.
Pour white sauce over entire casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a boiler over low heat until mixed thoroughly.

title: taco salad
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Shred lettuce.
Slice tomatoes into bite size pieces.
Chop onions.
Grate cheese.
Chill the first 6 items.
Just before serving, add crumbled corn chips and top with dressing.

title: expanding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Yields 2 gallons.
Can add rum to taste, if desired.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix/combine first five ingredients by hand.
Mix next three ingredients in separate bowl and then mix with dry ingredients by hand.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: holiday mocha fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar, butter and salt in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat; stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add the next 6 ingredients, stirring until marshmallows melt.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix all together. Put in refrigerator.

title: ada's pea salad
directions: Mix and serve.
Use your favorite salad dressing.
Other ingredients to suit your taste.
Happy cooking.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Sprinkle ham and cheese in pie shell. Beat eggs, cream, salt, pepper and basil until mixed but not frothy.
Pour over ham and cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until set.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Place broccoli in greased baking dish.
Make stuffing according to package directions and place over broccoli.
Place cheese on top of stuffing.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over cheese. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour, until bubbly.

title: president john f. kennedy fish chowder
directions: Simmer haddock in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Drain; reserve broth.
Remove bones from fish.
Saute diced pork until crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Saute onions in pork fat until golden brown.
Add fish, potatoes, celery, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Pour in fish broth plus enough water to make 3 cups liquid.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add butter and milk.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with diced pork.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until soft.
Add evaporated milk, margarine and salt and pepper to taste.
Add cheese.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken and soups, then fix stuffing as box says.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick lasagne
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook onion, garlic and oregano. Add soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer for 30 minutes or longer. Stir now and then.
In shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch), arrange 3 alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (or longer, the longer the better).
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients and then gradually add the next 3. Continue blending. Stir in last 3 ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
In a different mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs.
Add dry mixture and softened butter.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean (approximately 45 to 55 minutes) in a 350° oven.

title: double berry delight
directions: Whirl all ingredients in a blender until thick and smooth.

title: fiery bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Microwave at 50% power for 10 minutes, stirring several times. Garnish with green onions. Serve with tortilla chips. Serves 8 (6 if someone is greedy).

title: mints
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Then mold or cut.

title: "dog bones"
directions: Melt chocolate, peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Have Chex in large bowl and pour mixture over.
Mix until well coated. Have sugar in brown paper bag.
Pour Chex mix in and shake. Pour into bowl and serve.

title: chocolate coconut bars
directions: Combine the crumbs, butter and sugar. Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except nuts; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Pour nuts evenly over top of filling.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: lemon honey glazed chicken
directions: Rinse chicken with cold water, pat dry and sprinkle with paprika.
Place two lemon slices on each piece and arrange in a circle in a round microwave dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 6 - 7 minutes or until done, rearranging chicken after 4 minutes.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Remove to serving dish when done.
Cover and keep warm.
In small microwave bowl, combine honey, mustard, onion, lemon juice and curry powder. Microwave on high for 3 minutes or until bubbly.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Serve with rice and favorite vegetable.

title: breakfast sausage souffle
directions: Brown the sausage until cooked and broken up with a fork. Drain and set aside.
Place bread slices in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Layer sausage over bread.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt and pour over bread and sausage.
Top with cheese and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Souffle will brown and rise.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Mix sugar, tomato juice, flour and onion together; pour over hot dogs in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve on heated platter with toothpicks stuck in hot dogs.

title: black bread(russia)
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Place in bread machine, use bread program, press start. Makes 1 1/2 pound loaf. You may also bake in oven at 375 until brown on top.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine ingredients; put dough in greased baking pan and bake at 375° for one hour.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Cool.

title: swedish glazed nuts
directions: Before preparing meringue, spread nuts in a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and toast in a 325° oven for 8 minutes.
During this time, beat egg whites to a froth.
Add a dash of salt. Add sugar and a generous teaspoon of cinnamon to the meringue.

title: almond toffee delight
directions: Boil butter, margarine and sugar for 2 minutes.
Line jelly roll pan with foil, then line with club crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle 1 package chopped almonds on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cut when warm, take out of pan when cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer cooked sausage on top of bread.
Layer grated cheese on top.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Pour over cheese.
Bake slowly at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Melt butter; add onions, garlic powder and seasoning salt. Heat on high until onions become soft.
Add potatoes; stir and cover, stirring occasionally.
Once potatoes become soft, add parsley flakes.
Brown well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch fluted cake pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In mixing bowl, using electric mixer, beat together the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until mixture is light and fluffy.
Using mixer at low speed, beat in milk powder, flour, soda and cinnamon, beating until thoroughly combined.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to combine.
Pour batter into sprayed cake pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes (until cake tester inserted in middle comes out clean).
Let cake cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Remove cake from pan; set on wire rack.
Let cool for at least 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hobo beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces. Brown and drain. Brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Add vinegar, brown sugar, ketchup, white sugar, drained kidney beans, drained butter beans and baked beans. Mix all together and bake in greased casserole for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion in 4-quart Dutch oven until beef is light brown.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer stirring occasionally until spaghetti is tender about 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: brew
directions: In a large pitcher, combine orange soda and cranberry apple drink.
Serve over ice cubes.
Makes 5 cups.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans and juice into paste.
Mix together all ingredients except nuts.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until top browns.

title: 12 loaves of bread
directions: Knead 15 to 30 minutes.
Let double in size.
Make into loaves to double again.
Coat tops with oil before baking.
Bake at 350° until brown and sounds shallow by gently thumping center.
These freeze well.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and canned milk in a heavy pan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Quickly add vanilla and marshmallows and beat until well blended and marshmallows are melted.
Add nuts.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool.
Yield: approximately 1 1/2 pounds.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil the spaghetti according to package directions, but add a bit of vegetable oil.
Drain and refrigerate overnight in covered container.
(It is important the spaghetti be well cooled in order to work with it.)
Chop the cucumber, onions, green pepper, pimento and eggs very thin. Combine and mix with the spaghetti. Combine the salt, pepper, celery seed and oregano and mix with the spaghetti.

title: oreo delight
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine.
Crush all Oreos except 6. Place crushed Oreos over top of melted margarine.
Mix instant pudding according to directions and pour over cookies.
Cover pudding with Cool Whip completely.
Use 6 remaining cookies for decorating either by crushing them or leaving whole.
Store in refrigerator.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice and orange juice.
Blend bananas with part of this juice. Mix water, sugar, all juices and bananas until sugar is dissolved.
Pour in round container.
Freeze 24 hours. Pour in punch bowl.
Add 64 oz.
Sprite and mix until mushy. Delicious!

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt one stick margarine.
Add cookie crumbs and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Allow to chill for about 20 minutes in refrigerator. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 cup of Cool Whip. Spread on cookie crust.
Beat pudding with milk until smooth. Spread pudding on second layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top. Garnish with grated chocolate, if desired.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and oil and add eggs and flavoring.
Then add flour. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 450° until light brown.

title: sparkling fruit juice punch
directions: Combine all and put in ice.

title: stuffed mushrooms italiano
directions: Wash the mushrooms and remove the stems.
Chop the stems and put them in a mixing bowl.
Add the butter, onions, garlic, pepperoni and green pepper.
Cook, covered, on High in the microwave oven for 2-3 minutes.
Stir in the cracker crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper, and mix well.
Spoon the mixture into the mushroom caps and cook, covered, on Medium in the microwave for 4 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Variation:
Substitute	1/2 envelope dry onion soup mix for taco seasoning and onion.
Omit dressing.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak crumbs and oatmeal in milk.
Add meat, egg, onion, and seasonings.
Mix well.
Put in pan to bake.
Cover with catsup and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour milk pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients into blender, cover, and process on MIX until well blended.
Bake on a lightly greased griddle until nicely browned.
Turn only once.
Yield: 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water until dissolved.
Mix in marshmallows, seven-up drained pineapple (1/2 can).
Put in refrigerator until congealed.

title: carolina chicken
directions: Layer 11 x 14 pan with chipped beef. Wrap chicken breasts in bacon and put on top of chipped beef. Mix cream of mushroom soup with sour cream and cooking sherry. Spoon this mixture over the chicken and cover with foil. Cook at 300° for 2 hours. Open to brown. Serve over wild rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir, cover and bake in a slow oven at 275° for 5 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add sour cream, egg and vanilla and mix well.
Place peaches in pie shell and cover with sour cream mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: asparagus dish
directions: Mix together and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° in a buttered baking dish.

title: bundt fruitcake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, mixing well. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in chopped fruit and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Remove.

title: grandma fleissner's egg pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend well.
Heat frying pan and coat with butter.
Pour in mixture and cook until top is firm and bottom is lightly browned.
Flip over and brown other side.
Place on a plate and put on your favorite syrup, or roll up, slice and enjoy!
Makes 4 to 5 (6 to 7-inch) pancakes.

title: three layer dessert
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pea and corn casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potted venison
directions: Trim venison of all fat.
Cut into 3-inch cubes.
In a large kettle, heat olive oil and add meat.
Brown on all sides.
Add garlic and shallots.
Mix well until light brown.
Add wine and simmer uncovered until wine is reduced by half, about 20 minutes at medium heat.
Add beef stock and Worcestershire sauce with whole mushrooms.
Mix and cover.
Simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.
Remove from heat.
Place in serving bowl and serve with Hunter Sauce on the side.
Nice served with roasted potatoes.

title: easy oven barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in roasting pan.
Layer onions and pour on sauce made from remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: ropa vieja(cuba dish - "old clothes")
directions: Combine steak, onion quarters and water in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups of liquid; cool. Shred meat mixture with two forks; set aside.
Place 2 whole pimentos in an electric blender; process until smooth and set aside.
Cook green peppers, onion strips and garlic in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pureed pimentos, tomato puree, bay leaves and cooking wine; cook 3 minutes.
Stir in shredded meat and 1 1/2 cups of reserved liquid.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Serve over hot fluffy rice; garnish with pimentos and peas.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Simply pour your strawberries and any liquid in the package into a bowl and stir in the lemon juice and Splenda. Mash your strawberries a little with a fork, if you'd like. Yield: 8 servings.

title: carrots deluxe
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan. Add lemon juice. Arrange carrots in layers in a baking dish.
Between each layer, pour in the lemon juice and margarine mixture. Sprinkle with chives and parsley. Add the water. Cover and bake at 350° until the carrots are tender, about 50 minutes.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate, 10
x
1/2-inches.
Cook
and stir beef, onions and chopped green
peppers over medium heat until browned; drain. Stir
in seasoning mix.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds
in
blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into
plate.
Bake
25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5
minutes.
Serve
with sour
cream,
chopped
tomatoes
and shredded lettuce, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together well and cook over medium heat in heavy saucepan until ball forms.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: salmon pate
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones and skin.
Flake the salmon.
Add cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, salt and liquid smoke.
Mix well; chill overnight.
Shape into log; combine pecans and parsley.
Roll salmon log in pecan mixture; chill overnight.

title: shrimp and scallops in sauce(low-fat)
directions: Mix flour and milk together.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Saute scallops in 1 teaspoon butter 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Saute shrimp in 1 teaspoon butter 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Pour milk mixture into hot pan and cook until the mixture thickens.
Add sherry and seasonings and turn down the heat.
Add seafood and simmer 5 minutes.
Spray individual casseroles with cooking spray. Add seafood mixture.
Sprinkle top with paprika and bake 20 minutes.
Serve with crusty bread and salad.
Serves 4.

title: quickie dessert
directions: Pour pie filling in baking dish.
Add seasons.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Bake until brown.

title: grape-nut bread
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in milk for 1/2 hour.
Mix in dry ingredients. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until dry when tested with a toothpick.
Can be frozen.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add buttermilk to make a thick batter a little at a time. Drop into enough hot cooking oil to deep fry.
When brown, place on paper towel.

title: chile verde
directions: Fry pork until brown.
Drain off grease.

title: chicken or tuna salad
directions: Mix and soak gelatin in cold water.
Warm can of soup.
Mix gelatin and soup; cool.
Add salad dressing and chicken mixture. Pour over eggs, sliced in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until set.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: diet corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Mix corn meal, oil and egg yolk.
Beat egg white stiff and fold in.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and place in oven until margarine melts (do not burn). Pat chicken pieces dry with paper towels.
With tongs, dip chicken in melted margarine.
Place, skin side up, in baking pan. In a small bowl, mix potato flakes and seasonings.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Do not turn during baking.

title: overnight salmon casserole
directions: Place half the bread cubes in bottom of buttered shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together salmon, onion, celery, green pepper, olives and mayonnaise.
Spread over bread cubes.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Beat eggs. Blend in milk and soup.
Pour over salmon and bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and spread with shredded cheese and return to oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: best biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk. Stir very carefully, not too much.
Turn dough onto floured counter; knead lightly!
Roll out to 1-inch thickness.
Cut with a drinking glass.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using 2 tablespoons butter, grease a 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Rinse and pick over berries. Dry on paper towel before spreading over the butter and sugar.
In a mixing bowl, cream together the remaining 6 tablespoons butter, the remaining 1/2 cup sugar, egg, vanilla and orange rind.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a small bowl.
Add half of the flour mixture and half of the milk to the batter.
Stir just until blended.
Add remaining flour and milk and, again, lightly mix.
Pour batter over cranberries.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool on a cake rack 20 minutes before turning out onto a serving dish.
Serves 8.

title: spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw spinach and squeeze out all the water from spinach.
Add all ingredients except butter.
Open box of filo dough.
Place one sheet at a time on a cookie sheet.
Use approximately 8 to 10 sheets for bottom layer, then spread all ingredients.
Place another 8 to 10 layers of filo dough on top, buttering each sheet.
Place in refrigerator for about 10 minutes until butter hardens.
Cut the pie, then cook it for about 1/2 hour.
You can also freeze the pie once it is cooked!

title: carrot-pineapple salad
directions: Combine the ingredients and chill before serving.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot in bowl; mix Miracle Whip, milk and sugar in another bowl.
Add more milk, if not creamy enough.
Add to cabbage and mix together.
Refrigerate until served.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Spread in baking dish. Spread layer of rice and layer of mixed vegetables.
Spread soup over top.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese browns.

title: raised biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and add liquids.
Put in bowl and store in fridge.
Roll very thin; cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each biscuit in melted butter and place double decker in pan.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake the same as biscuits, at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburg patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into patties.
Cook until done.

title: vegetable fritters(chinese)
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil in medium mixing bowl.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain fritters on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: wedding punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 4 minutes.
Add orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice and bananas.
Freeze mixture and store in freezer.
Add ginger ale when serving.
Yields 50 servings.

title: york beach shrimp
directions: Melt margarine; pour over pasta.
Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and toss.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole; add remaining ingredients over pasta.
Heat under broiler about 5 minutes.

title: crispy fried fish
directions: Stir together cornmeal, salt and pepper in a shallow dish. In another bowl, beat egg, add water and blend well. Coat fish pieces in seasoned cornmeal, dip in egg mixture. Coat pieces again with cornmeal. Fry a few pieces of fish at a time in hot oil until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: refrigerator pickles(no-cook)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix and pour over pickles the salt, celery salt, sugar and white vinegar.
Let pickles stand at room temperature for a few hours; stir occasionally.
Use any jar for storing in the refrigerator.

title: cheese straws #3
directions: Mix
cheese,
butter
and red pepper, then add flour, 1 cup at a	time.
Place
on
cookie
sheets after shaping into straws. Bake at 400° until set.

title: mother's bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to boiling point and pour over bread.
Beat well. Add eggs, sugar and butter.
Mix well and add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: date bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg to mixture.
Pour boiling water over cut-up dates and add 1 teaspoon of soda to this mixture.
Add alternately with flour, other teaspoon of soda and salt to creamed mixture.
Add nuts last.
Bake in 2 large greased loaf pans in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Turn out of pans to cool.
Wrap when cooled.
This keeps well.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: Fry okra in 2 tablespoons shortening for about 20 minutes. In another saucepan, make roux with remaining shortening and flour.
Add onions, celery and garlic.
Cook until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add okra, tomatoes, parsley, bay leaf, thyme, sweet basil and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper. Add peeled, deveined and washed shrimp and crabs (break off and crack the claws and cut the body in half).
Simmer 10 minutes longer.
Add oysters and sausage; let simmer for 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in file just before serving.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain grease.
Add tomato soup and mushroom soup.
Cook noodles separately in salt water until tender.
Add hamburger mixture.
Add slices of cheese on top to melt soon as casserole has finished baking.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine; add pretzels. Press into 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: double boiler frosting
directions: Place over boiling water and beat until mixture stands in stiff peaks.
Scrape bottom and side of pan occasionally.
Fold in 1 teaspoon of vanilla.

title: lemon asparagus chicken
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Set aside.
Spoon off fat.
In skillet, combine soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles.
Garnish with lemon wedges and fresh thyme, if desired. Serves 4.

title: danish browned potatoes
directions: Melt butter in small frying pan.
Add sugar.
Cook and stir until browned.
Add potatoes.
Cook and stir until potatoes are lightly browned.
Season with salt.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Add crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Fold in coconut.
Chill well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 greased 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pans in oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni (do not use cheese) in an 8-inch skillet.
Add hamburger and onion.
Cook until onion is done.
Stir in tomato soup and seasoning.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
In a serving bowl, add tomato mixture to macaroni.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Blend well. Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Do not beat in mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 325° for one and a half hours.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Boil rhubarb and water until rhubarb is soft and mushy. Strain off juice.
Taste and add the sugar (more if desired).
Add the juices.
Chill.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in microwave.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Stir, then cook until mixture boils.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Remove; add baking soda and stir.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Combine butter and cheese; mix well. Add flour, cereal, salt and red pepper; stir until all ingredients are well blended. Shape mixture into 1/2 inch balls; place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Dip a fork in flour and flatten balls slightly. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove to wire racks and cool completely. Store in an airtight container up to 1 week.

title: wilma's oatmeal scotchies(pan cookies)
directions: Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla extract; gradually add remaining ingredients (flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon).
Stir in oats and butterscotch morsels.
Spread into baking pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 35 (2-inch) squares.

title: triple chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 13 x 9-inch baking pan with foil set aside.
In bowl combine 1 c. flour and sugar, but in butter until crumbly.
Press on bottom of pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
In another bowl, beat milk, cocoa, eggs, remaining 1/4 c. flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Mix in chocolate pieces and nuts. Spread over prepared crust.
Bake for 20 minutes or until set. Cool.
Use foil to lift out of pan.
Decorate with icing if desired.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Drizzle oil over crackers while stirring.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shake well.
Store in sealed container.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add celery and onion to beef and cabbage.
Brown, then add beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer until juice is about 4 tablespoons.
Serve with mashed potatoes and corn bread.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt the chocolate and butter in a double boiler.
Mix the flour, sugar and salt; stir into chocolate.
Add the milk slowly, stirring constantly, until fully thickened, about 15 minutes. Beat the egg yolks well.
Stir in a little of the chocolate into the eggs; then return to the hot mixture and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool partially.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; then add 1/3 cup sugar until stiff.
Swirl the meringue over the pie.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Mix the 4 beans together in casserole.
Brown bacon or ham with onions.
Add mustard, ketchup, brown sugar and garlic powder and mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add to beans and mix together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Bring 1 c. water to boil, add tea bags and let boil 2 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
In tupperware container, mix sugar, orange juice and lemonade.
Add tea mixture and stir to melt. Slowly add remaining water and bourbon.
Mix well and place in freezer.

title: beef, bean and macaroni chili
directions: Fry ground beef and onions until lightly browned; drain off fat.
Chop tomatoes.
Add enough water to tomatoes and bean liquid to make 1 cup.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans, liquid, chili powder and macaroni to beef mixture.
Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes.

title: beet jelly
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 1 minute. Add sugar and gelatin. Boil 6 additional minutes. May be canned and sealed with lid or paraffin.

title: southern spicy gingerbread
directions: Add beaten eggs to the sugar, molasses and shortening.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add the hot water.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain; cover with cold water and set aside.
Crumble ground beef and sausage (use same skillet), brown and then drain.
Add 2/3 jar of sauce and Italian seasoning and mushrooms.
Simmer 5 minutes, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix cottage cheese and egg together and set aside. Spray bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch glass pan with Pam.

title: christmas salad
directions: Let all but whipping cream stand overnight.
When ready to serve; add whipped cream.

title: lightning fudge
directions: Sift powdered sugar.
Cut in butter into pieces.
In medium microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk. Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts, blending well. Spread evenly in buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Cool and cut in 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 pieces.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Melt cheese, soups and tomatoes together. Add chicken and noodles. Put in a large casserole dish and microwave on 50% power about 15 minutes. Crush Doritos on top.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes in a preheated oven with cover on at 425°, then drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Pour heated sauce over drained chicken; top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes, uncovered.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rocky road fudge brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions; stir in pecans.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle miniature marshmallows over hot brownies.
Combine chocolate, milk, and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate and butter melt, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Transfer to a medium mixing bowl.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla; beat at low speed until smooth.
(If frosting is too stiff for spreading consistency, add milk, 1 Tbsp. at a time, stirring until smooth.) Spread over brownies.
Cool in pan on a wire rack, and cut into bars.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chop and prepare broccoli; cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Melt butter in pan; add flour, chicken cubes and boiling water.
Stir; add broccoli, shredded cheese, half and half and salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 cup rice or cooked potatoes (optional).

title: viola's carrot cake
directions: Beat at high speed 3 minutes, then add 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup raisins.
Beat another minute.
Bake one hour in angel food cake pan (350°).
No grease or flour needed.

title: easy frosting
directions: Melt oleo; stir in sugar and milk.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Smooth on cake quickly.
Enough for a 9 x 12-inch cake.

title: white chocolate chunk cookies(first place family picnic '93)
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Drop dough by spoon onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or less, depending on size.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets; move to wire rack.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Finely grind peppers.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Boil mixture 6 minutes.
Add 2 boxes of fruit pectin.
Boil 3 more minutes. Remove from heat, skim and pour into hot sterilized jars.
Put on lids, seal and place sealed jars in hot water bath, with at least 1/2-inch covering jars.
Boil 5 minutes to process.
Remove from water.
Yields 4 pints.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Stir in cold milk gradually.
Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken.
Lower heat and continue to cook until filling has bubbled for 1 minute.
Add part of hot mixture to slightly beaten egg yolks.
Blend and return to saucepan.
Cook for 2 minutes over very low heat.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: irleen's peanut butter pie
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
When pudding is done, mix in peanut butter.
Pour in pie shell and let it cool.
Serve with whipped cream on top.
Refrigerate after serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and half of onion in skillet.
In large rectangular pan, line bottom with frozen tortillas.
Cover with browned hamburger and onion.
Spread chili over this.
Add layer of onions and the cheese.
Add another layer of frozen tortillas, sliced tamales and Mexican beans, layer of onions, Spanish rice, green chilies and more grated cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until heated thoroughly.
This dish is great reheated.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring, nuts and morsels.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°; reduce heat to 300°.
Place foil over top and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Top with icing recipe.

title: savory chicken on rice
directions: Fry chicken until brown in butter about 20 minutes.
Spoon out all but 3 tablespoons of fat.
Mix next 6 ingredients together and sprinkle over chicken.
Pour in bouillon.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add mushrooms with liquid.
Cook 5 minutes longer.

title: on the light side peanut butter fluffs
directions: Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine crumbs and margarine.
Press about 1 tablespoon of mixture into each cup.
Top each with about 2 teaspoons of whipped topping.
In a large bowl, with an electric mixer on low speed, mix milk and peanut butter together until smooth.
Add pudding mix and beat about 1 minute or until blended; fold in remaining whipped topping.
Distribute mixture among cups and freeze several hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for about 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Arrange chicken in 2 1/2 quart shallow oval casserole dish with meatier portions toward the edge of dish.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High for 16 to 18 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Let stand covered 5 minutes.
Remove chicken to warm platter.
Stir pineapple sauce to thicken slightly.
Spoon over chicken.

title: crispy nut cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients, sifting together 3 times.
Combine sugar, brown sugar and shortening; mix well.
Add egg and vanilla, stirring to make a smooth batter.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Add oats, nuts and coconut.
The mixture will be stiff.
Shape into balls, 1-inch diameter.
Bake on lightly greased cooking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: south seas dressing(the best ever)
directions: Blend well and chill.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cold pizza(great for parties!)
directions: Spread cream cheese on platter or dinner sized plate.
Cover with salsa.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables over and serve with nacho or tortilla chips.
Use any vegetables you like and be prepared to make more.
It doesn't last long!

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; add peas.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serve on lettuce, garnished with tomatoes and onion wedges.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Cream shortening and 1/3 cup of sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Quickly roll hot muffins in melted butter, then roll in mixture of 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Makes 1 dozen medium size muffins.

title: chicken and yellow rice for a crowd
directions: Boil chicken (do not use more or it will overwhelm dish).
I add bay leaves.
Boil until meat falls from bone.
Cool to touch. Remove chicken from bones.
Discard bay leaves.
Reserve 1-quart broth; add meat to broth.
Bring to boil.
Follow instructions on rice package.
Add rice to broth.
Bring to a boil and cook, uncovered, 1 to 2 minutes.
Lower heat, cover and cook approximately 20 minutes until rice is done.
Stir only to keep from sticking.
If you need to add water, be sure it's hot.
When done, remove from heat.

title: springerle(molded christmas cookies)
directions: Beat eggs until very light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; beat for 15 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Fold in anise extract and flour.
Roll dough 3/8-inch thick.
Thoroughly flour springerle mold or rolling pin.
Press molds firmly to dough.
Cut cookies apart and place on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Let dry overnight at room temperature, covered with paper towels or uncovered.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place cookies in oven and immediately reduce temperature to 300°.
Bake for 15 minutes. Cookies should not brown.
Store cookies 2 to 3 weeks to mellow flavor.
These cookies are very hard and may be used for dunking in coffee, tea or cocoa.
For Christmas, paint designs with egg yolk colored with food coloring.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cheesy chicken rolls
directions: Pound fillets to 1/4-inch thickness.
Pat fillets dry and spread on layer of cheese mixture.
Roll fillets in jelly roll style and roll opposite way with 1 strip of uncooked bacon to secure.
Place in casserole sprayed with Pam.
Bake 40 minutes or until juice runs clear.
Cheese will ooze out.
Place under broiler 20 to 30 seconds to crisp bacon.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine ingredients until it makes a stiff dough.
Roll very thin on a floured surface; let stand.
Roll up and cut slices 1/4-inch wide.
Unroll and let dry 2 hours.
Drop in broth and cook.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on cocktail bread.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use with crackers as a dip, or hollow out a loaf of round rye bread.
Cut inside of bread into cubes.
Fill center with dip; serve bread around plate as dippers.

title: cold oven pound cake(no baking powder)
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar and beat well.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each added egg. Add 1/2 of flour and 1/2 of milk.
Add balance of flour and milk; add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (glass dish 325°). When cake comes out of the oven, pour 1 bag of small marshmallows on cake (I use 7-ounce jar of Marshmallow Creme).

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Beat eggs with a fork in a large bowl.
Add sweet potatoes, pineapple and raisins.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well and no flour can be seen.
Place in 13 x 9-inch greased dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: delicious carrot salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together and let set at least 2 hours. More honey may be added if desired.

title: butterscotch pinwheels
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Crisco in double boiler.
Remove from heat; add milk, flour and vanilla.
Blend and spread in a 15 x 10-inch pan, greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Dump out on a towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Spread filling and roll up jelly roll style.
Cool and slice.

title: easy one-dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, the ham and onion powder in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix baking powder mix and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: tiny sour cream biscuits
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour, sour cream and cheese. Spray tiny muffin pans with Pam and spoon mixture about halfway filling the tin.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm for better flavor.

title: canoe bean salad
directions: Drain first 5 ingredients.
Lightly stir together.
Add sliced onion and salad dressing to taste.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broiler cheese flops
directions: Combine cheese, bacon, onion, green pepper, eggs and lunchmeat in grinder or food processor.
Blend until well chopped, but not pureed.
Add chili sauce and mix well.

title: taco salad
directions: Heat beans, add a little water and stir until heated. Add corn and seasoning mix or Texas Pete. Heat and stir. Heat taco shells in 300° oven for a few minutes. To serve two large portions - crumble two shells in bowl and top with 1/2 beans and corn. Add sour cream, lettuce, onions, tomato and salsa to taste. Only 5 points per person. Total points for entire recipe - 9 1/2.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Prepare mixture in a large pot.
Add squash, onions and peppers; bring to a boil.
Cook about 15 minutes or until tender. Put in jars and seal.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add meal, salt and sugar and mix until lumps disappear.
Fold in eggs and add milk.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potatoes with cheese and chives
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes; put in boiling water, drain and mash.
Place in large pan; season with salt, pepper and garlic. Ladle with butter, sprinkle with Cheddar, garnish with chives. Bake just until cheese melts.

title: beef barley mushroom soup
directions: In 3-quart covered saucepan cook mushrooms, green pepper, onion and garlic in butter or margarine about 5 minutes or until tender but not brown.
Add cooked beef; stir in barley, sage and salt.
Add broth; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until barley is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In large bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan, layer lettuce, carrots, onion, celery and peas.
Mix salad dressing, vinegar and sour cream.
Add a layer of dressing mixture.
Add another layer of ingredients.
Top with bacon bits and Parmesan cheese.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend listed ingredients.
Add one medium carton Cool Whip. Freeze in ring mold or flat pan.
Keeps for a long time in freezer, covered.
Take out just shortly before serving.
Put leftover back in freezer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems; chop enough stems to measure 1/2 cup and set aside.
Cook mushroom caps over medium heat in margarine about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine cream cheese and Blue cheese; mix well.
Stir in chopped stems and onion, if desired.
Fill mushroom caps with cheese mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and broil until golden brown.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and melted butter by hand (I use a pastry blender) until crumbly and crumbs stick together.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for top.
Beat eggs and add with milk to remaining crumb mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with fruit pie mix.
Sprinkle with the reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: icicle cucumber pickles
directions: Wash, peel, seed and slice cucumbers.
Soak in lime water for 24 hours.
Wash well and drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar and spices. Pour over cucumbers and soak 2 hours.
Put over heat, boil 1 hour or until clear.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: hush puppies with onions
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion and beaten egg. Pour boiling water over this mixture, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add more water if necessary.
Drop by spoonful into deep, hot fat.
You can double ingredient for larger amount.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl the Cool Whip, lemon juice, Eagle Brand milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Lightly beat eggs, salt and pepper.
Stir in onions, meat, sprouts, green onions and soy sauce (1 tablespoon).
Heat oil in skillet.
Use a ladle and drop 1/4 cup of the mixture into this oil.
Fry until browned on both sides.
Drain.
Mix the cornstarch to a paste with a little broth.
Combine in a saucepan with remaining broth, molasses and remaining soy sauce.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour over patties and serve.

title: delicious fudge cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together and set aside.
Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Stir chocolate into boiling water to dissolve.
To creamed mixture, alternately add flour, buttermilk and chocolate, blending well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Boil peeled potatoes 10 minutes.
Drain.
Put in fresh water. Add broth, all the seasonings and cook until potatoes are tender. Put milk in double boiler and add flour and butter when hot.
Stir until thick.
Pour into the potato mix and bring to a boil.

title: overnite oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat the first 8 ingredients. Add oatmeal, flour, coconut and raisins. Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cut Crisco into mixture until well mixed.
Take out 1/2 cup of this mixture and save.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into a greased pan or 2 (8-inch) cake pans. Add chopped pecans to the 1/2 cup of dry mixture and sprinkle over the top of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Always serve hot.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Brown and drain fat.
Add to meat onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until transparent.
Then add salt, pepper, oregano, chopped tomatoes, tomato sauce and parsley.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot over cooked spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Yields 6 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk that has been heated.
Add vanilla.
Spread a little of egg white over crust and pour in egg and sugar mixture.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes, until brown. Will make 1 deep-dish pie or 2 small pies.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Beat eggs well.
Mix.
Mash bananas. Alternate mixing flour mixture with bananas.
Bake 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.
Oven setting is 350°.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones.
Place chicken in a large baking dish.
Spoon soup over the chicken.
Mix dressing according to the directions.
Place on top of chicken and soup. Pour some of the broth that you cooked chicken in over the dressing.
Dot with margarine and bake 35 to 45 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti as package directs and drain.
Stir margarine into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into crust in buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust.
Cook beef, onion and pepper until done.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat.
Turn mixture into spaghetti crust.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat together sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in apples, pecans and vanilla.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan onto cake plate.
Make glaze and spoon hot glaze over hot cake.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in greased/floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 inch pan for 1 hour.

title: cheese icing for finger bread
directions: Put all ingredients together in mixer and beat until smooth. Cut bread (either Texas toast size or plain slice) in finger slices (3 to one slice).
Cut off crusts.
Spread cheese mixture on all sides (top and sides only; do not do the bottom).
Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven (370° to 375°) for about six minutes or until lightly browned.
(Should be eaten hot).

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and butter and beat well.
Add milk and corn.
Grease baking dish with butter.
Place in 350° oven and bake about 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir gently when about half done.
It is best to bake immediately before serving.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Place in crock-pot, cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with your favorite chips.

title: minestrone
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain and set aside.
In an 8-quart kettle, saute onion, celery, parsley and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in next eight ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir in cooked beef, zucchini, all three beans and spaghetti.
Simmer, covered for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender and spaghetti is cooked.
Spoon into individual bowls and top with Parmesan cheese. Yields 5 quarts.

title: fresh apple cake with butter pecan glaze
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat together sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Add flour mixture slowly.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour batter into pan.
