Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack.
Remove from pan.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Make as much as you need.
Spray casserole dish the size to fit your family.
Slice potatoes to make first layer in dish. Slice onions to make second layer.
Slice squash for third layer; slice peeled fresh tomatoes for fourth layer.
Sprinkle with margarine, salt and pepper.
Add layers in order to fill your dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Works well in microwave.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dough will be stiff.
Roll out on floured surface and cut with small cutter.
These do not rise or spread, so can be placed close together on cookie sheet.
Make small indentation and put dab of tart jelly on each before baking. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.

title: tupperware fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in all ingredients and press in pan (any desired size).

title: coffee custard
directions: Combine custard mix, Equal, instant coffee and cinnamon in medium saucepan.
Stir in skim milk.
Cook on medium-low heat until mixture comes to a full boil, stirring constantly.
(Mix will be thin.)
Pour into custard cups or dessert dishes. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until set.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first three ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; stir constantly. Cover; cook 3 minutes without stirring; uncover and boil 5 minutes. (Do not stir.) Remove from heat; add morsels; stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla. Blend well. Pour into 13 x 9 buttered dish. Let cool. Yields 3 pounds.

title: jerome's chocolate pound cake
directions: Have eggs and butter at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Cream shortening and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together; add these alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into tube pan; cook for 80 or 90 minutes.

title: old fashioned chicken pie
directions: Add the salt to the flour.
Mix the shortening with the flour and salt.
Mix with real warm water.
Knead until real leathery. Roll real thin and drop into boiling broth.
Pour into baking dish. Slice boiled eggs on top.

title: summer squash bread
directions: Steam 10 to 12 minutes or microwave 5 minutes the squash and onion until tender.
Drain and finely chop or mash vegetables. Add margarine and set aside.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients well and put in a hot iron skillet.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Check with a toothpick or fork for doneness.

title: chicken and dumplings(the very best!)
directions: Beat eggs and margarine real good.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and enough water to make a good dough.
Chill.
Roll out thin and cut in strips, then cut strips about 2 inches long.
Cook chicken and debone.
Put back in broth.
Add dumplings and boil for 5 minutes.
Warm 1 can of cream of chicken soup and 1 cup milk.
Add this to chicken and dumplings and cover and simmer for 1 hour.
I double this recipe for family.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In medium saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening into flour, until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves side of bowl.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove from bone and pull apart. Place into casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup and spread over chicken.
Mix crackers and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter with powdered sugar until it crumbs. Reserve 1/2 cup for topping. Spread peanut butter on crust. Cover with vanilla instant pudding. Then top with Cool Whip and crumbs.

title: prize winning burrito bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease deep dish pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Mix Bisquick, water and beans.
Spread mixture in pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients on bean mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at
a time, beating after each addition.	Sift together flour, salt
and baking
powder.
Add

Add vanilla. Pour

10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.	(Makes a large cake.)

title: zucchini bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Bisquick, egg substitute, buttermilk and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in all remaining ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix
well
sugar,

salt, dried mustard and vinegar. Add onion juice (if you don't have any onion juice, just put about 3 or 4 tablespoons of diced onions and a couple tablespoons of water in a blender and mix well to make juice).
Add vegetable oil
slowly (very,
very slowly), as you mix with an electric mixer constantly until thickened.
Add poppy seed.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring above ingredients to a boil.
Pour warm dressing over drained vegetables.

title: hawaiian-banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until batter is moistened.
Spoon into greased and floured pan (two pans: 9 x 5 x 3-inch or one pan: 9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 1 1/2 hours at 360° or until brown.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O
as
directed
on box, pineapple with juice, canned milk,
cottage
cheese, cherries (no juice), pecans and mayonnaise.
Chill in large casserole dish or 2 small dishes.

title: swedish cream
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Heat to steaming point.
Cool until it begins to thicken.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Stir well.
Serve topped with fresh strawberries or fruit in season.

title: frozen peach treat
directions: Place peach slices not touching each other on baking sheet and freeze about 1 1/2 hours until hard. Put in blender or food processor; add yogurt and sugar and process about 1 minute until smooth. Spoon into dessert bowls; sprinkle with coconut and top with mint sprigs. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini in a large bowl. Mix well and make a hole in the center and add flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder, chocolate morsels and nuts.

title: fettucine poppke(serves 2)
directions: Heat water in Dutch oven (to cook pasta).
Melt butter in heavy saucepan. Stir in flour to form roux.
Add white pepper. Add broth.
Blend mixture. Remove from heat.
Add half and half. Blend and return to low heat. Slowly add grated cheeses. Stir constantly for smooth blend until dissolved. Serve immediately with cooked pasta.

title: beef teriyaki and rice
directions: Mix soy sauce, sherry, brown sugar and seasonings; add beef, let stand 10 minutes to marinate.
Stir fry beef in hot oil in skillet until browned.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Mix broth and cornstarch, add to skillet.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Prepare rice according to package.
Serve meat mixture over rice.

title: cordon bleu hamburgers
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk until softened.
Combine softened bread crumbs, meat, pepper, celery salt and egg.
Shape into 12 thin patties.
Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese on top of each of 6 of the patties.
Cover with remaining patties, gently pressing together edges of patties to seal ham and cheese inside. Broil.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Place in foil:
Form ground beef into 4 patties, place onion slice on beef patties, carrots or potatoes, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Blend ingredients.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles; seal perforations.
Spread mixture over dough.
Roll as jelly roll. Slice roll in 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: no hassle wassail
directions: Combine cider, apricot nectar, rum, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon in large stock pan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 1 hour.
Pour into punch bowl.
Stud several oranges with cloves; float in punch.
Makes approximately 30 servings.

title: josie's chicken
directions: Saute pepper, celery and onion in 2 tablespoons of oil, add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice to as many as 6 hungry people and wait for the compliments that are sure to follow.

title: homemade butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, then add yellow.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Fill canister with milk.

title: cathie mcmahon's bran muffins
directions: Use a really large bowl to mix wet ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Fill muffin tins with papers and fill.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Cut shortening into mixture. Add the buttermilk; mix with fork until a dough forms. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Knead until smooth. Pat dough to 3/4-inch thick. Cut out biscuits. Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp feta
directions: In a large skillet with cover, saute onion and garlic in butter and oil until golden.
Stir in tomatoes, dill, basil, mustard, sugar, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 to 8 minutes.
Add shrimp and wine.
Continue simmering, stirring about 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp cooks through (don't overcook).
Turn off heat; sprinkle crumbled Feta in skillet.
Cover and let sit two minutes. Serve over rice with crusty bread and green salad.

title: anna mae's strawberry crunch
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add crushed crackers and pecans.
Pour into buttered 9x13-inch dish.
Bake 15-20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pineapple polish or turkey sausage
directions: Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and pineapple juice.
Bring to a boil to make syrup.
Saute first 3 ingredients in oil or margarine until wilted.
(Do not cook.)
Put sauteed ingredients in casserole dish, 13 x 9 x 2, with pineapple chunks.
Pour syrup over ingredients in dish.

title: strawberry delight
directions: First Layer:
Crush graham crackers, butter and sugar together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: salmon log(cocktail spread)
directions: Combine all ingredients except the parsley and walnuts in blender; mix well.
Place in bowl and chill for several hours. Shape into a log.
Sprinkle parsley and walnuts over log and serve.
Serve with assorted crackers and Melba toast.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, mix soft shortening, sugar, unbeaten eggs, extract and vanilla.
Mix 2 1/2 minutes, then add alternately flour mixture and buttermilk.
Beat 2 1/2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf or tube pan.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt together.
In large bowl combine butter and sugar; beat until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown meat and add salt; drain excess fat off.
Simmer meat and beans for 10 minutes.
Set to one side and chop up the first 4 ingredients and toss well.
Grate cheese and add to first mixture.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water gradually, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thick. Reduce heat; cook 2 or 3 minutes longer, until clear and transparent.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and red food coloring.
Fold in sliced strawberries.
Garnish top of pie.

title: taglarini
directions: Brown meat in large pan; add onion, garlic and green pepper. Cook 5 to 10 minutes. Add mushrooms, juice, puree and corn. Bring to a boil and add noodles. Cook at a simmer about 10 minutes. (Stir frequently to keep from scorching.) Pour into greased baking dish not more than 2-inches deep. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and slightly browned. Serves 15. Cut recipe in half for less. Will freeze well.

title: old-fashioned soft sour cream cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and lemon juice. Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream; blend well.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar or nuts, if desired.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 dozen and Praise the Lord!

title: orange pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels with melted butter.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese.
Beat cheese with sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled pretzel base and refrigerate.
Mix together orange jello with hot water.
Add juice from mandarin oranges to jello and let cool until partially set.
Add mandarin oranges and pour over partially set cream cheese mixture.

title: pork chops with corn dressing
directions: Put corn in mixing bowl.
Add onion, egg, salt and sugar; mix. Cut bread in cubes; add to corn mixture to make stiff enough to hold shape.
Brown chops; salt to taste.
Drain off excess fat. Divide dressing into 6 parts; heap one part on each chop.
Pour water around chops, not on dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in covered dish.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Brown chicken breasts on both sides.
Leave meat side down and add salt, pepper, onion powder and garlic powder.
Sprinkle parsley and tarragon on top.
Add slice of onion, then tomato on top of each breast.
Top with scallions and mushrooms.
Pour 1 cup wine and optional brandy over chicken.
(Alcohol will all cook away.)
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Uncover and simmer 15 minutes. (If too much liquid, add a bit of flour and water; if too dry, add wine.
In both cases, cook 10 minutes more.)
Serve with rice.
Add green salad and crusty bread for a delicious meal!
Can be made in advance a few days, refrigerated and reheated.
Easy guest dinner!

title: funeral potatoes
directions: Mix together margarine, soup and sour cream.
Add potatoes and cheese.
Place in a greased 9 x 11-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: talarene
directions: Brown onion in butter and meat and cook until browned. Add tomato sauce and water.
Add noodles and cook until noodles are done.
More water may be added to keep moist.
Add olives and mushrooms.
Pour into large, buttered casserole and cover with sharp cheese.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand in oven 15 minutes after heat is off before serving.

title: sweet 'n' sassy beans
directions: Start grill, allowing it to reach a temperature of 250 degrees, or preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: apple dumpling cobbler
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and separate. Wrap each apple quarter with crescent roll dough and place in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.

title: ruth clark pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Combine with salt in a large bowl; weight with a plate.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, drain off liquid, but do not rinse.
Heat until warm.
Mix sugar, vinegar, pepper and celery seed.
Pour over pickles and let stand overnight.
Pour in jars and store in refrigerator.

title: apple-cranberry dish
directions: Place first four ingredients in a baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour and nuts together and sprinkle over apple mixture. Slice margarine over the top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, corn meal, salt, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Cook in a slow 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes in uncooked pie shell.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cook everything else until cheese melts.
Spread in baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
With wet hands, shape into a roll about 2 1/2 inches across.
Roll in 1/3 cup fine graham cracker crumbs.
Wrap tightly in waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes about 8 servings, allowing two 1/2-inch slices for each.
Top with whipped cream.

title: hawaiian cheese ball
directions: Put aside 1 cup nuts.
Mix all other ingredients together. Roll into a ball form. Roll ball in the remaining 1 cup of nuts. Refrigerate.

title: potato candy
directions: Put mashed potatoes in medium to large size mixing bowl (one small to medium potato).
At this point, you would add the walnut or vanilla extract.
Add powdered sugar, a little at a time, and mix well after each addition.
Mixture will at first, start getting runnier.
After several additions of powdered sugar until mixture is about the consistency of bread or biscuit dough, approximately a 2 pound bag or box, or just under.

title: bar-b-que beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour entire contents of the cans of pinto beans into a casserole (with a lid).
Dissolve the cornstarch in a small bowl with the 2 Tbsp. water.
Add this solution to the beans and stir.
Add the remaining ingredients to the dish, stir well and cover.
Bake for 90 minutes or until the sauce thickens.
Stir every 30 min.
After removing the beans from the oven, let the beans cool for 5 - 10 min. before serving. Serves

title: oven chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces in melted butter.
Combine corn flake crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in this mixture. Place in buttered pan and brown in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle a few drops of water on browned chicken pieces.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: grandma's baked manicotti
directions: Mix eggs and parsley in large bowl.
Add salt, Parmesan and Ricotta cheeses and onion.
Mix well.
Stuff the uncooked manicotti shells with the cheese mixture.
Preheat oven to 400°. Pour half the tomato sauce onto baking dish.
Arrange the stuffed manicotti in the pan.
Pour the rest of tomato sauce over the manicotti.
Cover and bake for about 20 minutes.
You may sprinkle Parmesan cheese over manicotti immediately before serving.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: hot crab dip(microwave)
directions: Mix all together.
Heat in microwave until blended.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups. Beat egg.
Stir in milk and oil. Mix in remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from pans.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all together in casserole.
Melt margarine and crumble 3 to 4 slices of bread into it.
Spread on top of pineapple mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown crumbled sausage in pan; drain and cool.
Place into mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fudgy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a full boil for 1 minute.
Add salt and vanilla.
Blend peanut butter.
Add oats and nuts and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper to cool.

title: ham spread
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Add ham until chopped.
If necessary, stop blender during process and push ingredients off sides and toward center.
Makes 1 cup.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Divide batter in half (in two different bowls).
In one, add 1/2 cup melted margarine and 1/2 of milk.
Pour this batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Melt caramels and 1/2 cup margarine.
Add the remaining milk.
Pour over cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Check for doneness with toothpick.
Really delicious.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Use same part salad dressing and sour cream.
Best mixed a day ahead.
Lasts a long time.

title: "killer-burritos"
directions: Spray baking pan with no-stick oil.
In a large bowl, mix well:
refried beans with sausage and 1/2 bag Cheddar cheese. Spread (completely) on fajita shells.
Roll up like pinwheels.

title: mary's chicken rolls
directions: Three pounds of chicken breasts are easier.

title: gobs
directions: Put in pan and cook until thick the flour and enough milk to make a paste.
Add the rest of
the milk and cook until it thickens. Stir at all times. Take off and let set until cold.
Add the sugar and beat with mixer until smooth. Add the Crisco, salt and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
The longer you beat it, the fluffier it gets.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put onion and celery on top of beef.
Combine other ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours. Pour off fat, shred, and return to roaster.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: For sauce, mix mayo, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over all remaining ingredients, mix and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer ingredients (may thin with chicken broth).
Top with layer of dry dressing.
Pour melted butter over dry dressing. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff soup
directions: Saute beef and onion until brown.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
If using fresh mushrooms, slice and saute during last few minutes of simmer.
Remove onion and beef from drippings. Turn heat to medium; blend in sour cream, salt and pepper.
Add beef stock, mushrooms, beef, onion and noodles.
Heat until steaming.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all cake ingredients in electric mixer bowl and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean and loaves are golden brown.
Leave loaves in pan and prick all over with a toothpick.

title: hot buttered apple rum
directions: Tie spices in a spice bag or cheesecloth.
In a 3 1/2 or larger crock-pot, put spice bag, apple juice, rum and sugar.
Cover; cook on low heat setting for 7 to 8 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours. Discard spice bag.
Ladle hot punch into cups.
Float about 1/2 teaspoon of butter atop each serving.
Makes 10 (6-ounce) servings.

title: cousin nina's cheese cake(easy and good)
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with sugar, vanilla, and lemon juice.
Mix in eggs.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until center is set.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling or serve plain.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger; season to taste.
Dip tortillas in boiling water.
Roll hamburger in tortilla.
Place in an 8 x 11-inch pan. Spread chopped green peppers and cheese on top.
Combine soup and milk; heat until smooth.
Pour over enchiladas and bake until cheese is melted.

title: ruth's cucumber chow chow
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over drained cucumber mixture.
Cook for 35 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars.

title: pumpkin custard cake
directions: Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, water and 3 eggs.
Blend as directed on package.
In small mixing bowl, beat pumpkin and 2 eggs.
Pour evenly over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: date bread
directions: Add dates and soda to boiling water and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf tin at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Cut butter in 4 or 5 pieces.
Put in top of double boiler with egg yolks and lemon juice.
Let stand at room temperature for 1/2 hour or more.
Just before serving, heat over gently boiling water 1 1/2 minutes, stirring briskly with wooden spoon.
Serve at once over broccoli or asparagus.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Mix in flour with hand until dough is easy to handle (that's why it is 6 1/2 to 7 cups of flour).
Place, greased-side up, in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth; place in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before baking, shape dough into rolls.
Cover and let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Heat oven to 400° and bake 25 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen medium rolls.
(No kneading; fresh rolls every night.)

title: city chicken
directions: Trim fat off the cubed pork and beef.
Alternate pork and beef cubes on wooden skewers.
Salt and pepper meat to taste.
Dip skewered meat into beaten eggs, then coat with ground saltine crackers.
Brown into skillet until brown on all sides.
Put into a roaster.
Add a little water to the roaster and bake in 350° oven for approximately 3 hours or until meat is soft/done.

title: lower salt, lower fat chili
directions: Crumble and brown ground beef with onion. Add beef broth and water. Bring to a boil.
Pour into deep bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Fat will form solid plate on top. Remove and discard.
Stir chili mix and tomato paste into beef mixture. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of washed green peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Precook peppers in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
(For crisp peppers, omit precooking.)
Brown meat with onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stuff bell peppers; place in baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: irish cream
directions: Brand name ingredients are very, very important in this recipe, especially the condensed milk and the chocolate syrup.
It really tastes better when you use the better ingredients.

title: carrot-orange muffins
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Put all ingredients in a nonstick frying pan.
Cook at medium temperature, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes dough-like and pulls away from sides of the pan.
Remove from the pan and cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: dill dip in rye
directions: Mix the cream cheese, green olives, onion, dried dill weed, garlic salt and mayonnaise.
Stir in milk to dipping consistency. Chill.
Scoop out center of loaf of rye bread.
Cut center into cubes for dipping.
This can also be served with raw vegetables.

title: no fat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin tin(s) with butter spray. In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
"Sift" with a fork. Gently stir in yogurt and water.
(Add fruit, if desired.)
Blend just until moistened.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until well browned.
Yields 12 regular muffins.

title: double chocolate banana muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine bananas, oil, and egg; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Fill greased or papered muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until muffins test done.
Yield: about 1 dozen.

title: country style cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Grease 9-inch skillet with shortening or oil. (Use bacon drippings if available.) Leave oil in bottom of pan. Place pan in oven to heat. Combine cornmeal, eggs, buttermilk and melted bacon drippings. Whisk well. Pour into hot skillet. Batter will sizzle. Bake at 450° for 35 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in 400° oven until fork-tender.
Meanwhile, cook bacon until crisp; drain then crumble.
Measure drippings and add salad oil to drippings to make 2/3 cups.

title: brick chili cheese dip
directions: Melt chili with Ro-Tel; add cheese.
Cook on low heat until well blended.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix well the lettuce pieces, American cheese (grated), hamburger, kidney beans and onion slices.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions, stir in some salt.
Add mayonnaise and vinegar.
Mix together until you have creamy cucumbers.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours to mix flavors.
Serve cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Hull the berries.
Mash one pint and leave the other pint whole.
If some of the berries are too large, cut them in half. Bake pie shell according to directions on the back.
To mashed berries, add 3 tablespoons cornstarch and boil the mixture about 5 to 10 minutes until thick and clear.
Keep stirring.
Line baked shell with the whole berries.
Pour hot mixture over shell and berries.
Chill 1 to 2 hours and spread whipped cream over pie. Leave out one berry for the top as decoration.

title: chuck wagon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add lightly beaten egg and vanilla. Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add grated apple.
Form into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sunshine chicken(on the grill)
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine mustard, pineapple juice and brown sugar, mixing until sugar is dissolved.
Wrap each chicken piece with bacon, fastening with wooden picks.
Brush mustard sauce over chicken and bacon.
Grill over hot coals about 10 minutes, turning frequently, while brushing with additional mustard sauce.
Remove wooden picks.
To serve, spoon remaining sauce over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Stir into creamed mixture just until blended. (Do not overmix.) Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with nuts and chips. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cream puffs
directions: Pour boiling water over butter in a saucepan; place over heat and stir until butter melts.
Add flour all at once and stir constantly with a wooden spoon until the mixture leaves the side of the pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating to a smooth paste after each one. Then beat the mixture until smooth and velvety.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet, keeping about 3-inches apart.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes or until well puffed and delicately browned, then reduce the heat to 300° (slow) from 30 to 40 minutes longer.
This will cook the centers thoroughly, but puffs should become no browner.
Remove to a cake rack to cool. When cold, cut off tops with a sharp knife.
Fill with cream filling, whipped cream or ice cream and replace tops.
Makes 10 large cream puffs.

title: egg dish souffle(prepare the night before)
directions: Beat eggs in milk. Stir in other ingredients.
Empty into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake 45 minutes, uncovered, in a 350° oven.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand while mixing rest of cake.
Cream together margarine, sugars and eggs and add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix oatmeal mixture with above and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in an oblong pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a casserole dish.
Bring broth, salt, pepper and chicken soup to a boil.
Pour over chicken. Scatter peas/carrots on top of all the mixture.

title: nutty brussels sprouts
directions: In 2-quart casserole, cook Brussels sprouts and water at High for 10 to 11 minutes, or until tender.
Cut each Brussels sprout in half and separate the leaves.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease pan (13 x 9-inch). Spread mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Let cool slightly and cut into pieces.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in blender.
Turn to high speed and add ice cubes, one at a time.
Serve when smooth.
Makes about 2 servings.

title: crescents
directions: In a large glass or Pyrex bowl, mix flour, yeast, salt and sugar.
Add hot water.
Add beaten eggs and oil.
Beat 3 minutes. Add additional flour, starting with 2 cups.
Stir.
Add flour until dough is no longer sticky.
Knead 5 minutes.

title: pork chops with spanish rice
directions: Trim fat off chops; brown.
Sprinkle seasonings over meat. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese on top.

title: red hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers.
Pack peppers into 1 cup.
Add juice to make one cup.
Cook sugar, peppers and vinegar hard for 10 minutes. After sugar has melted, keep stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add Certo.
Pour into jars.
Seal with paraffin.

title: salted pecan icing(for yellow cake layers)
directions: Cream butter with one box powdered sugar.
Mix a little water with it to make it of spreading consistency and add pecans.
Makes enough for 3 layers.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello as box directs; set aside 1/4 cup.
Mix jello, strawberries and pineapple; let set in mold.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Mix well; pour over the layered spinach/strawberries and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ann's sand cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and water; add flour and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Form small rolls 1 1/2 inches long. Bake on ungreased sheet at 300° for 20 minutes until delicately browned.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: squash bake
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add butter, onion, sour cream, soup and 1/2-3/4 bag of stuffing mix.
Mix completely. Pour into oblong casserole 9x13.

title: old fashioned shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13 baking dish. Combine first 4 ingredients plus brown sugar and stir until blended. Add shortening by cutting in, as for pie dough. Combine eggs, buttermilk and vanilla and stir into dry mixture just until blended. There will be some lumps. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and stir in crushed pineapple.
Add 1 cup of nuts, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt.
Form into ball or roll and cover with remaining nuts.
Make 1 or 2 days ahead before serving.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place 4 quarts of popped popcorn in large grocery bag.
In a 2-quart microwave dish, put sugar, oleo and corn syrup.
Place in microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring to dissolve sugar and oleo.
Then microwave on High for 4 minutes; do not stir. Remove from microwave; add 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Stir well.
Pour over popcorn and stir with wooden spoon; fold top of bag.
Shake and insert into microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Stop after 45 seconds; remove bag, shake and return to microwave for remaining 45 seconds.
Empty into large pan and stir until cool.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until done.
Drain on paper towel.
Saute onion in small amount of bacon fat.
Dice enough bacon to yield 1/2 cup. Mix remaining ingredients and place in 1-quart casserole.
Cut remaining bacon into thirds and place on top of bean mixture. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crumble cookies up in long pan.
Mix cream cheese and condensed milk together.
Put on top of cookies, then add Cool Whip.
Add more cookie crumbs.
Top with cherries or blueberries.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in bread pan.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: tourtier'e(french pork pie)
directions: Fry pork and drain.
Season with cinnamon, ginger, salt and pepper.
Mix with mashed potatoes.
Place in pie crust and top with the other crust.
Poke with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Then continue to bake at 350° for another 15 minutes. Serve hot with Cheddar cheese.

title: healthy baked chicken breast
directions: Pound each chicken breast.
Layer each breast with the following: thin slice of ham, chopped fresh tomato, flavored bread crumbs and Mozzarella cheese.
Roll each and fasten with toothpicks.
Place in Pam sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, Mozzarella cheese and Mrs. Dash or pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber-dill pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Chill until serving time.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut stem and circle out of top of peppers.
Remove seeds and inside pulp.
Combine rice, meat, 1 1/2 cups of onion, salt and pepper and mix well.
Stuff peppers with this.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Cook pinto beans overnight in crock-pot.
Drain excess water. Mash beans until refried bean texture. Fry chorizo in frypan, no grease needed; until comes apart totally. Add to beans.
Cut cheese in cubes.
Add to beans; stir occasionally until melted. Keep warm while serving.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: meat ball yummies
directions: Combine beef, bread, egg and 2 tablespoons of sauce.
Mix and shape into balls.
Brown in oil in a nonstick skillet.
Drain. Combine 1/3 cup sauce, butter and sugar with meatballs. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes about 25 meatballs.

title: black-eyed appetizer salad
directions: Soak and cook black-eyed peas.
Drain.
Cool peas quickly, uncovered.
Drizzle artichoke marinade over peas.
Cut hearts to bite-size and add to mixture along with radishes, celery and onions.
Add just enough French dressing to cover and salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate before serving.
Spoon onto lettuce to serve.
Makes enough for 8 salads.

title: grecian orange cake
directions: Mix.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: eggplant parmesian
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice eggplant in 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices lengthwise.
Dip each slice first into eggs, then into crumbs.
Saute in hot oil until golden brown on each side.
Place layer of eggplant in 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, oregano and mushrooms.
Place layer of Mozzarella over mushrooms.
Cover well with some of the tomato sauce.
Repeat until all eggplant is used.
Top last layer of sauce with rest of Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour or until sauce is bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: three cheese potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onions in a 13 x 9 pan.
Combine Parmesan cheese and 3/4 cup each Cheddar and Mozzarella, sprinkle over potatoes and onions.
Top with bacon, butter, salt and pepper. Bake for 35-40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining cheeses.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Split frankfurters.
Spread very lightly with mustard; insert a strip of cheese in each.
Roll pastry thin; cut into 6 inch squares.
Place 1 frankfurter diagonally on each square.
Bring together other 2 diagonal corners of pastry so that ends of frankfurters are exposed.
Put onto baking sheet; glaze with egg or milk.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for pork or chicken
directions: Brown meat in skillet. Place in baking dish. Blend other ingredients and pour over meat. Cover and bake in a moderate oven 30 minutes or until meat is done.

title: venison stew
directions: This is better if cooked outside in a small wash pot or kettle. Put bacon in kettle and cook until tender.
Put venison, potatoes and onions next.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with water and cook until almost done.
Add sausage and cook until done.
Add eggs, one at a time and cook well.
Don't stir too much while cooking.
Serve hot.

title: mama's dump cake
directions: Will need a well greased sheet cake pan.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Arrange berries in pie shell.
Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Mix until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes longer or until mixture is clear and thick.
Add gelatin. Stir until completely dissolved.
Pour mixture, while hot, over strawberries.
Chill until set.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: clam chowder(serves 6 generously)
directions: To large pot, add bacon, onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Saute gently for 5 minutes.
Now, add bay leaf, liquid from clams, water, diced potatoes, Lea & Perrins, salt and pepper; simmer until potatoes are barely tender.
Combine oil and flour; stir into chowder until thick.
Add clams, cream and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Remove bay leaf if you can find it.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Except for onion, mix all ingredients (by hand) well.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Fry in small amount of fat with onion over medium heat until brown, turning frequently.
Serve with gravy made from drippings.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Start with beef; brown and drain off fat.
Then add cooked noodles and rest of ingredients.
Serve with salad and bread. Fast, easy 1-pan dinner.

title: bologna
directions: Mix hamburg and Tender Quick.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Next morning, add remaining ingredients.
Divide into 4 rolls (long).
Bake 2 hours at 250°.
Turn every half hour while cooking.

title: pastry
directions: Mix; roll out and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: mexican cold dip
directions: Spread bean dip in bottom of serving dish.
Add layer made up of avocados, pepper, salt and lemon juice.
Add third layer made up of sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Make top layer of onions, tomatoes and olives.
Sprinkle cheese over top and serve with corn chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble 1 sleeve of crackers in casserole pan bottom.
Mix sour cream, chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup with bite size chicken.
Pour over cracker base.
Crumble 1 sleeve crackers.
Put on top.
Bake in a 375° oven until crackers brown.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place the apples, 1/2 cup sugar and the flour in a baking dish. Top with a mixture of the oatmeal, sifted flour, brown sugar, granulated sugar and butter or oleo.
Bake at 375° until apples are done.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Mix with flour and salt.
Chill. Roll very thin and cut with 2-inch cookie cutter.
Spread with anchovy paste, deviled ham, sardines, hot salsa or whatever filling desired.
Fold over and bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 20.

title: missouri casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put one layer of potatoes to cover bottom of casserole.
Add 1/3 of sliced onions, then a layer of ground chuck.
Continue with two more layers; cover the top with tomato soup with 1 teaspoon sugar added.
A small amount of water may be added to rinse soup cans.
Cover and bake in 325° oven 1 3/4 hours or in 350° oven about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are done.

title: hamantashen
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Add alternately with milk.
Chill dough.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake to box directions; cool.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Combine ingredients in blender until frothy.
Before serving, combine mixture with 1/2 cup crushed ice for each serving.
Yields 48 ounces.

title: chicken piccata
directions: With a sharp knife, remove skin and white pith from lemon and discard.
Working over a bowl, cut lemon segments from their surrounding membranes.
Chop segments coarsely and reserve with the juice.

title: aioli sauce
directions: With marble mortar and pestle or blender (less gourmet), crush garlic cloves to paste.
Add egg yolks and salt; work in the mustard.

title: broccoli, turkey and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together except 1/2 cup cheese.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip the chicken in eggs, then flour and back into eggs, then bread crumbs and fry in olive oil until browned.
Put a thin layer of sauce in the bottom of a baking dish, 12 x 9-inch.
Place the chicken in one single layer; spoon on spaghetti sauce and place a single layer of cheese and more spaghetti sauce on each piece of chicken.
Put the chicken in the oven at the same time as you put the spaghetti on to boil (350°) and they will be done at the same time.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in a 9 x 13-inch cooking dish.
Pour powdered cake mix on top of peaches.
Spread out.
Spread melted margarine on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Sprinkle sugar on top of cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach pie (olive oil)(spanakopita)
directions: Clean and wash spinach; allow to drain.
Chop spinach in a large mixing bowl.
Brown onion in olive oil.
Beat eggs; add to spinach.
Break white Feta cheese into small pieces; mix with spinach.
Add browned onions to mixture; season to taste.
Melt butter; mix with olive oil.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; place 6 pastry sheets into pan, brushing each with the butter-oil mixture. Spread spinach mixture; cover with 6 individually greased pastry sheets.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Serves 15.

title: eleanor's lattice top casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 can onion rings and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Unwrap crescent rolls and separate into 2 rectangles; press perforated cuts together and cut into strips (pizza cutter works well). Place strips on top of casserole to form latticed top. Bake for 15 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onion rings. Bake 5 minutes more or until lattice is golden brown.

title: rick's breakfast eggs
directions: Mix eggs, tortillas and cheese.
Cook over medium-high heat in nonstick skillet until almost set.
Stir often.
Add salsa and finish cooking.

title: freezer cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to rolling boil in 1 qt. saucepan.

Stir in flour. Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute; remove from heat. Add eggs; beat until smooth. Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Freeze uncovered until solid, about 4 hours. Place frozen puffs in freezer bag. Seal and label; freeze up to 1 month. 10 puffs.
1 1/4 hours before serving, heat oven to 400°. Place desired number of puffs 3 inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake until puffed & golden, 45-50 minutes. Fill puffs with sweetened whipped cream, fruit pie filling, or ice cream.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pickled squash
directions: Mix squash and onions.
Sprinkle with salt; cover with ice. Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar, mustard, celery seed and turmeric; heat well.
Add squash and onions; bring to a boil.
Cook for about 5 minutes, stirring thoroughly once. Put into hot jars and seal.

title: borsch
directions: Simmer mushrooms in 3 cups water for 1 hour.
Strain and through cloth and save stock.
Wash mushrooms thoroughly and save. Saute 1 chopped onion in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil until golden. Add beets, carrot, celery, all chopped.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add 6 boiling cups water, 1 whole onion, bay leaf, peppercorns, lemon or vinegar and tomato paste.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove the whole onion, pepper, carrots and bay leaf.
Add mushroom stock and salt to taste.
Cool to let flavor "marry."
Serve cold or reheat.
Add mushrooms and dollop of sour cream to each serving.
Makes 8 or 10 servings.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine milk and oats.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.
Add oil and eggs, mixing well.
Stir in dry ingredients until moistened.
Bake on hot, lightly oiled griddle.
Makes 10 to 12 cakes.

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, red apples, pineapple, marshmallows, celery and enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.

title: sagnala
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix soup and milk together.
Mix tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix together.
In casserole dish, put 1/2 package raw noodles in bottom, 1/2 of hamburger and 1/2 of shredded cheese.
Repeat again.
Then top with soup and milk mixture and finally, tomato sauce mixture.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375° or until browned in 9 x 13 pan.

title: cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring salted water to rolling boil and slowly stir in grits.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in butter and garlic cheese.
Put eggs in cup and add milk to make 1 cup. Beat well.
Add to grits mixture.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: no-peek chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine both soups, water and rice in bottom of baking pan that is of a large size and is buttered. Cover tightly with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Bake for 2 hours in 325° oven.
Don't peek.

title: country-style chicken dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine frozen potatoes and 1/2 can French fried onions.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute beef, stirring with fork to keep texture loose, pour off excess fat. Cut vegetables into cubes. Add remaining ingredients to meat and enough juice from peas to keep ingredients moist. Bake in greased casserole 1
1/2 hours at 350 degrees until carrots are tender.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix the pudding into the pineapple with juice.
Add a can of fruit cocktail or whatever fruit you wish.
Bananas can be used at last minute just before serving.
Let stand awhile or overnight. Fresh fruit can be used also.

title: vanilla wafer fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and vanilla wafers. Add the other ingredients. Pack in pan lined with wax paper. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: (Do not substitute ingredients for a lower fat variety as this will drastically change the consistency.)

title: stuffed potatoes cacciatore
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Prick with fork.
Cook uncovered in microwave on 100% power, 13 to 16 minutes.
Let potatoes sit while making sauce.
Combine zucchini, onion, garlic and water in covered container.
Cook on High, 3 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Stir in chicken and both cans of tomatoes and Italian seasonings. Cook covered 5 to 7 minutes until heated through.
Split potatoes. Mash centers.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon sauce on top, then sprinkle with cheese.
Return to microwave to melt cheese.

title: german flannel cakes
directions: *Milk may be soured by use of tablespoon of white vinegar.

title: muscadine cake
directions: While cake is hot, punch holes in cake with knife.
Spoon icing over cake.

title: texas cake
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, sour cream, salt, sugar, baking soda and eggs.
In pan, bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water. Add this boiled mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a cookie sheet that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: maine carrot cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Add carrots and nuts; beat well.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 pan. Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Servings:

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove stems.
Chop stems and set aside.
Cook sausage in skillet, chopping up finely, until browned.
Remove meat from pan.
Add mushroom stems to pan.
Cook on medium heat for 2 minutes.
Add sausage; mix.
Remove from heat.
Add cheeses and bread crumbs.
Mix; let cool.
Brush outside of caps with butter and stuff with sausage mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 450° in preheated oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be frozen and cooked directly from freezer for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Place layer of chicken in casserole.
Then a layer of broccoli.
Combine soup, curry, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Cover top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: e-z chicken rice(low-fat too)
directions: Put water in frying pan.
Add onion and pepper strips.
Cover and cook until tender, remove.
Add chicken and cook 10 minutes. Turn and add peppers, onions and gravy; simmer 10 or 15 minutes (or longer).
Pour rice in dish.
Arrange chicken and gravy over top.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Can use eggbeater.
Batter will be smooth and thin.
Spread thinly on griddle.
Bake on hot griddle.
Use oil or shortening sparingly. Serve with butter and maple syrup.

title: mincemeat
directions: Have mixture of first 4 ingredients come to a boil, then let simmer 1 hour.
To this mixture, add the remainder of ingredients.
Have mixture come to a boil and boil 10 minutes. Pack in clean jars.
Screw on bands tight.
Process in water bath for 30 minutes.
This is out of the old Kerr Canning book we used in the 40's.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9 pan with Pam.
Roll crescent rolls out on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and egg yolk.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Spread crescent rolls over cream cheese mixture.
Beat egg white and spread over rolls.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over rolls.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Best if made one day before serving.

title: mammy bowle's sugar cookies(light sugar cookie)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill before rolling out dough.
It will cut better.
Sprinkle cinnamon sugar on dough as you roll it out thin and cut out desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes. You can leave off cinnamon sugar if you plan to put frosting on cookies.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Add flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Spread onto greased cookie sheet.
Brush unbeaten egg white over batter.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, the longer, the crispier.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 boxes Jell-O, pecans and coconut.
Add enough Eagle Brand milk to hold together.
Form into small balls.
Roll balls in remaining 1/2 box of Jell-O.

title: fig nelson's
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well. Add flour, potato starch and baking powder.
Shape into two rolls and place side by side on a cookie sheet.
Make a slight indention down the middle of each roll.
Fill with fig jam (or any other jam).
Bake at 350° until slightly golden.
Cut, while warm, in slices on a slant, one finger wide.
Let cool and store in a dry, tight container.

title: down east bbq sauce
directions: Pour 4
cups vinegar into pot and bring to boil.
Empty black pepper, red pepper and salt into vinegar jug;
then pour hot vinegar back into jug; let stand approximately 10 minutes. Shake well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Roll a teaspoon of mixture into ball and press flat (crisscross).
Top with M&M.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain on paper towels.
Heat soup (do not dilute).
Add hamburger mixture when it bubbles.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Put Tater Tots on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat
in eggs, 2 at a time. Add vanilla, almond, flour, salt and baking powder.
Reserve 1 cup batter.
Spread remaining batter in greased jellyroll pan. Drop 1 can
cherry
pie filling over batter.
Dollop remaining batter over pie filling
here
and there.	Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Drizzle
with
powdered
sugar glaze.
Freezes well. Good warm or cold.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil the noodles for 15 minutes.
Drain and put noodles in a bowl.
Slice vegetables.
Pour in Italian dressing and mix with noodles, only about half or 3/4 of the bottle. Put in cucumber, black olives and tomatoes.
Mix with noodles.
Put in fridge until ready to eat.

title: hearty french onion soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter; stir in onions.
Cook until onions are translucent and slightly browned.
Stir in brown sauce and heat to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.
When ready to serve, ladle into ovenproof bowls; top with bread and cheese.
Brown cheese under broiler.
Serve immediately.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and pie filling in 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all cut butter into pats spread evenly over cake mix. Top with nuts.
Bake 350 at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread on your favorite meats.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe dish. Microwave on High, stirring twice, for about 7 to 8 minutes or until cucumber is crisp and tender and onion is transparent. Ladle into glass jars rinsed in hot water to prevent cracking. Cover and cool slightly before refrigerating.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Melt oleo, add sugar and cocoa and milk, stirring slowly. Bring to hard boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream shortening with sugar; add 2 eggs and 1 egg yolk (keep white).
Sift flour and salt and add.
Roll 1/4 dough at a time (thin).
Cut with cookie cutter.
Brush with egg white.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and add pecans if desired.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: braised sirloin tip roast
directions: Rub roast with flour.
Melt butter in a roasting pan.
Brown meat well.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons salt and pepper.
Add onions, bay laves, garlic and water.
Cover; cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes.
Sprinkle with remaining salt.
Cook, covered, for 1 more hour until tender. Serves 6.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature. Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla well. Add Cool Whip and mix well. Put in graham cracker crust. Top with cherry pie filling. Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Prepare a 9 x 13 pan and preheat oven to 350°. Prepare potatoes and set aside. Melt cheese with milk and set aside. Fry bacon, then sausage; drain meat and with 2 tablespoons of drippings, fry onions and mix bacon, sausage and onion in the skillet. In prepared pan, layer half of potatoes, then 1/3 of cheese, last half of potatoes and rest of cheese. Sprinkle meat and onion mixture over the top and bake until meat starts to look crusty.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add pineapple.
When partially set, add Cool Whip, cheese and coconut.
Let set for 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Saute onions until they are transparent.
Slice wieners in half and place on a cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Pour barbecue sauce over wieners.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon-orange delight cake
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve jello in water.
Add eggs beat 2 minutes.
Add cake mix; beat 1 minute.
Add oil; beat 1 minute. Pour into greased 9x13 inch pan.

Bake at 375° for 35-40 minutes. Mix confectioners sugar and orange juice while cake is still hot. Put fork marks in cake; pour sugar mixture into holes. Serve with Cool Whip and a cherry on each piece.

title: banana coconut crunch
directions: While beating egg whites, add sugar and beat until stiff. Crush vanilla wafers.
Add to egg whites along with coconut, nuts, salt and vanilla.
Spread into a well-buttered, large pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Slice 1 or 2 bananas on top and add Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: molasses corn puffs
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl. Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture is in coarse crumbs.
Pour molasses into measuring cup.
Add milk to make 1/2 cup.
Add liquids to dry ingredients.
Mix with fork until dough clings together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes until golden and baked through.
Cool slightly on wire rack.
Serve warm or cool completely and serve cold.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake on greased pizza pan for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: vinegar cobbler
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, oleo and water in a 2-quart boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Mix flour with cold water to make a semi-stiff dough. Roll out on a floured pastry sheet.
Cut into small pieces.
Drop dough into boiling vinegar mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold dry pudding mix into Cool Whip.
Add pineapple with juice and marshmallows.
Almonds and 1/4 cup chopped cherries may be folded in or use almonds and cherries as a garnish.

title: virginia chicken-apple salad
directions: Dip apples in lemon juice.
Combine with chicken, grapes, celery, olives and almonds.
Blend mayonnaise and whipped cream with 2 tablespoons lemon juice and salt.
Toss with chicken.
Best served cold with buttered croissants.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes about 100 servings.

title: katie's almond onion dip
directions: Blend ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.
Serve dip in a hollowed out bread loaf with fresh vegetables and bread chunks for dipping. This is a quick and easy dip that is very tasty.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt oleo and saute onions until tender.
Add bell peppers; cook a few minutes.
Add soups and chopped tomatoes.
Get all ingredients real hot, then add raw rice and shrimp.
Add parsley flakes.
Pour all this into a 3 to 4-quart casserole dish with cover or a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spray pan with Pam and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Rice should appear fluffy.

title: chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in pan in one layer.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mama's apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a well-greased round cake pan. Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ginger ale bread
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Let ginger ale lose its bubbles and add to mixture.
Pour into lightly greased bread pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix in sauce.
Put a layer of refried beans on bottom of pan.
Next a layer of hamburger.
Next a layer of sour cream.
Shred lettuce and put a layer on top of sour cream, followed by shredded cheese.
Put in fridge to set up.

title: turtle stew
directions: Cover turtle with water.
Put in 1 stick of margarine.
Cook turtle until you can take off bone.
Cook all other ingredients until done.
Then put all together and cook slow for an hour.
Cut up boiled eggs in it.

title: 5 layer delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, pecans and margarine and pack in bottom of 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: apple pudding with caramel sauce
directions: Cream sugar with margarine.
Add egg.
Sift together and add flour and cinnamon.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch (lightly greased) pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with warm Caramel Sauce.

title: slush punch
directions: Steep tea bags in 6 cups hot water for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze about 10 hours.

title: baked pancakes
directions: Gradually add flour to eggs, beating with rotary beater.
Stir in milk, melted butter and salt.
Grease a 9 or 10-inch skillet; bake in oven (450°) for 20 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve with hot fruit sauce or syrup.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Mix together graham crackers, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/3 cup butter.
Heat until thick the sugar, flour, milk and egg yolks, then stir in graham cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line pan with sliced peaches, 9 x 14 pan. Make batter of margarine, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, flour, baking powder and salt. Mix and spread batter over peaches. Mix 1 cup sugar in 1/2 cup water and pour over batter. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke frittata
directions: Saute onions, garlic, zucchini and mushrooms in butter and reserved artichoke hearts oil.
Beat eggs.
Blend in cheese and seasonings.
Fold in drained sauteed vegetables, artichokes and spinach.
Grease 10-inch quiche or pie plate.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips in microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir together.
Add nuts and drop on wax paper.
Let it sit until hardened and break apart.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Layer on top of corn bread the beans, onion, pepper, celery, tomato and bacon.
Mix together mayonnaise, pickle juice and relish.
Pour this mixture on top and lift edges slightly so it can soak in.
Chill.

title: fufu
directions: Mix the flour with water and make a smooth paste in a saucepan and cook it over medium heat, stirring all the time, until it thickens as desired.
Pour it into a wet bowl.
Shape into a ball. Serve with the peanut butter soup.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add beans, onion, celery and peppers.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and oil.
Stir gently.
Let set for at least 3 hours.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal in a large bowl or pot.
Stir. Then add sugar, molasses, salt and Crisco.
Stir and let stand until lukewarm.
Add 4 cups of flour and yeast.
Stir.
Then add remaining 4 cups of flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand until double, 3 to 4 hours.
Stir mixture and let rise again.
This will take less time.
Spoon into two large greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: cappuccino brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Butter a 9-inch square pan; line bottom with wax paper or parchment. Coat paper with butter and set aside. In a 4 to 5-quart saucepan over very low heat, stir together chocolate and butter until completely melted. Let cool slightly, then mix in sugar, Espresso, vanilla and eggs with a whisk. In a small bowl, whisk together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Add to chocolate mixture and stir until just combined (do not overmix). Fold in chocolate chips. Pour batter into prepared pan; bake on center rack until toothpick inserted in center comes out slightly wet with a few moist crumbs attached (30 to 40 minutes). Let cool completely. Run knife around edges; invert and cut.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl; mix well. Add enough broth for desired consistency. Spoon into buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
This makes enough for 6 people.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: In a blender container, combine undrained fruit cocktail and remaining ingredients.
Cover; blend until combined.
Add ice cubes; cover and blend until smooth.
Sprinkle with additional cinnamon (for garnish), if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, egg, crumbs, salt, pepper and 1/3 of the soup.
Put in pie pan; cook 25 minutes at 350° and drain off fat. Spread mashed potatoes over meat mixture; over potatoes, spread remainder of soup and 1/2 cup cheese and cook 10 minutes more.

title: pasta snacks
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the pasta in boiling, salted water until tender, yet firm, about 10 minutes.
If desired, keep the various shapes of pasta separate while cooking and frying.
Drain the pasta very thoroughly.
Fry pasta, a few pieces at a time, in deep Crisco heated to 365°.
Fry until pasta is golden, about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper toweling.
Immediately sprinkle generously with seasoned salt.
Serve warm or cool.

title: rice and green chilies
directions: Cook Rice.
Combine cooled rice with sour cream and chilies. Season to taste with salt and butter.
Arrange 1/2 mixture in buttered casserole dish; spread with 1/2 the cheese.
Then spread the rest of the rice; and the rest of the cheese.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Tear 1/2 angel food cake into small pieces and place in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour 1 can fruit cocktail on the cake.
Next, pour 1/2 of pudding in bowl.
Then place 1/2 of strawberries on top of the pudding.
Next, pour 1/2 Dream Whip on strawberries.
Pour in 1/2 of nuts, 1/2 coconut and 1/2 strawberry gelatin.
Now, repeat the same steps for the other half of the ingredients.

title: syrup pie
directions: Mix and bake in 300°
oven in an unbaked pie shell.

title: mushroom spinach dip
directions: In a bowl, combine spinach, sour cream, mayo, soup mix, mushrooms and onions and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Cook noodles.
Melt butter in skillet and add beef.
Cook beef until done.
Add tomato sauce.
Blend noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and mushrooms in large bowl.
Spoon into extra large casserole dish a layer of noodle mixture, then meat mixture.
Repeat layers and sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until mixture is heated and cheese melted.

title: lemon cream
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and salt; add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved; add lemonade.
Chill until partly set; fold in whipping cream.
Turn into 8 individual molds or one large mold. Chill until firm.
If desired, top each serving with a sprig of mint and a few raspberries or melon balls.

title: lazy crazy chocolate cake
directions: Add ingredients in order given.
Don't beat until all is added.
Beat like any ordinary cake. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Makes two 8-inch layers.

title: chicken continental
directions: Grease crock-pot with margarine. Place dried beef in bottom of crock. Wrap each breast with 1 slice of bacon and layer in crock over dried beef. Mix the soup, sour cream and flour; pour over chicken. Cook on low for 8 hours or 5 hours on high. Serve with Uncle Ben's wild rice.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Coat a medium skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms; cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook, uncovered, an additional 3 minutes or until liquid evaporates; set aside.

title: diabetic muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add honey, egg and milk.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Fill greased muffin pan.
Bake at 425° for about 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: everyday waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in egg yolks, milk and shortening. Fold in egg whites stiffly beaten.
Bake on hot waffle iron.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add sugar mixture to the sliced apples; toss to coat fruit.
Fill a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with apple mixture.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edge.
Sprinkle some sugar atop, if desired.
Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove foil; bake for 20 to 25 minutes more or until crust is golden.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and butter.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onion and pimento (optional).
Mix well.
Separate the crescent rolls into 4 rectangles. Seal perforations.
Put in bottom of pan.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture on each.

Pull corners together and seal. Brush with melted butter. Pour the can of cream of chicken soup diluted with the milk mixture over top. Top with crushed croutons and I also add some shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.
My guys love it!

title: squash pickles
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let set 1 hour and drain.
Then mix everything together.
Bring to boil. Put into jars and seal.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Stir into mixture candied cherries, chopped nuts and raisins.
Pour into 3 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: christmas punch
directions: Blend juices and water; chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Float a half gallon of lime sherbet on top of punch mixture.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick spray.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Cream margarine and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Alternately beat in flour mixture and milk until smooth.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet 1 1/2 to 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 9 minutes or until firmly set by lightly pressing finger on top (like a cake).

title: cheese melts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on cocktail rye slices. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.
(Makes enough to cover 1/2 package of cocktail rye.)

title: rice crispy delights
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Whip well with spoon.
Add dates, pecans and extract.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix. Pack into buttered pan.
Chill for 24 hours.
Cut and roll in coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: doughnuts ii
directions: **Use Gold Medal or Pillsbury bread flour.

title: indian pudding
directions: Bring milk to a boil. Add cornmeal.
Stir constantly until smooth and slightly thickened. Remove from stove. Add eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger and molasses.
Mix well.
Put into baking dish about 2-inches deep. Cover with wax paper.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 400° in a pan of water or until wax paper can be lifted without paper sticking.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: popover sausage
directions: Grease bottoms and sides of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside. Slice sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
In large skillet, brown sausage.
Drain on paper towels.
Meanwhile combine eggs, milk and oil.
Stir in flour and salt.
Beat with an electric mixer or by hand until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared dish.
Arrange sausage pieces in batter.
Bake in 400° oven about 35 minutes or until golden.
Serve immediately with maple syrup or Cheese Sauce. Serves 4.

title: chewy cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add flour and beat well.
Stir in pecans. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes. Cool 2 to 3 minutes on cookie sheet before removing to cooling rack.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Mix water, sugar, spices and fruit.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cider and heat.
Keep at simmering until ready to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix and cream together butter or oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs and grated zucchini and beat well.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and soda together and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
No frosting needed!

title: grilled potato packets
directions: Place sliced potato in center of large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Add onions, salt and pepper to taste; sprinkle bacon on top.
Fold up around potato mixture and seal well.
Allow to cook approximately 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Also can be placed on grill while you are grilling meat.
Place along edge of a hot grill.

title: cinnamon breakfast buns
directions: Night Before:
Grease a seamless angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.

About 5 p.m., remove the frozen bread dough from freezer. About 9 p.m., cut one loaf into about 20 pieces and place in pan. Cover with 2 tablespoons brown sugar, cinnamon, raisins or nuts, 1/2 of the pudding mix and 1/2 of the melted margarine.
Repeat on top of this layer with second loaf of bread dough and toppings. Leave overnight on kitchen table or counter, covered with a towel. Do not refrigerate.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add milk and vanilla.
Heat on stove and add eggs when mixture starts getting warm.
Cook until boiling and mixture will get very lumpy.
Put in mixer and whip with butter until fluffy and smooth.
Fold into baked pie shell.

title: strawberry pizza(so good)
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Mix these ingredients well and press into 12-inch pizza pan.
Flute edges.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Beat eggs and milk; add to sausage.
Cut crusts from bread slices and cube.
Add bread, salt, mustard and cheese to sausage mixture.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Saute onion, celery and peppers.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for several hours. Top with grated Monterey Jack cheese and/or sour cream. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat until well blended.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into cubes.
Layer chicken, then broccoli, then sauce on top. Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: confectioners candy
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together and add cream.
When batter is about the consistency of biscuit dough, add vanilla.
Color as desired.
Pinch off dough in bits about the size of a pecan.
Roll in hands and flatten slightly on waxed paper.
Top with 1/2 pecan. Yields approximately 36 pieces.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin strips.
In a skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook 1/2 the beef and onion until meat is no longer pink and onion is tender. Set aside.
Repeat with remaining meat, margarine and onion. Return meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup (undiluted) and paprika.
Heat through.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over hot cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil
sugar,
Karo
and
water until it forms a thread. Then add butter and nuts.
Then boil until a golden brown and nuts begin to pop.
Remove from fire and add vanilla and soda. Stir well; then pour out very thin.

title: pickles to freeze
directions: Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Stir now and then.
Put in small container and freeze.

title: orange slice - no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, margarine and orange slices with graham crackers and pecans in a large bowl in microwave for 5 minutes on defrost. Mix well until all is moist. Form into 2 loaves. Keep in refrigerator.

title: crunchy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly first 3 items; then mix eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
