To make batter stiff, use little more flour. Butter pans and bake in 400° oven until cookies are brown. Remove, cool and serve.

title: light fruitcake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, then add egg yolks that have been beaten until lemon colored.
Beat well, then add flour and wine alternately, reserving 1 cup flour to mix with the fruit. Add beaten egg whites last before adding fruit.
(Rub the cup of flour well into the fruit before adding to the batter.)
Bake from 2 to 3 hours in a very slow oven according to size of the cake. (Sift flour from 3 to 5 times.
You can add as many different nuts as you want.)

title: baked pineapple souffle
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Add pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Place in a buttered casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Toast bread in toaster or oven.
Place ham and cheese on bread.
Heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix soup, milk, vegetables, chicken, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir and then sprinkle with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until done.
Serves four.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Line bottom of pan with chopped nuts.
Separate biscuits and cut each into fourths.
Roll into ball.
Make sugar/cinnamon mixture in a Baggie and drop rolled balls into Baggie to coat well.
Put rolled balls in Bundt pan. Melt oleo with brown sugar and drizzle over dough balls in pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake tester is clean.
Turn onto cake plate when done; remove pan promptly.
Break pieces apart.

title: mexican dip
directions: Line
quiche
dish
with
the ingredients (in the order listed).
Bake
at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes and serve with chips.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and cut up chicken; mix with all other ingredients.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Crust comes to the top.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and put in baking dish.

title: jackie's cookies(drop pecan sugar cookies)
directions: Beat oil and butter until fluffy.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheets; press top with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: honey of a chicken salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients in large bowl.
In separate bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt, poppy seed, black pepper, lime juice and honey.
Add to chicken mixture.
Stir gently to blend. Chill before serving.
Serve over lettuce leaf.

title: cheesy zucchini
directions: Grease a shallow ovenproof baking dish. Wash and slice zucchini. Cook in boiling salted water for 3 to 4 minutes, then drain. Beat eggs and cream together in a bowl. Add the salt, pepper and nutmeg. Spread the zucchini into the baking dish.
Pour the egg mixture over them and sprinkle the grated cheese on top. Bake for 20 minutes at 200° C, 400° F or gas mark 6.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, ground pecans, sugar and butter.
Pat on bottom and 1 1/2-inch up sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup caramel syrup.
Add eggs and milk; beat until blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: kraft mac and cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to box directions; after done, add rest of ingredients.
Mix all together.
Let cool and eat.

title: sweet posies
directions: Melt butter in a small bowl.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in another small bowl.
Dip each biscuit into butter and then in sugar mixture.
Place biscuits, 1 inch apart, on a greased baking sheet. Place point of kitchen shears in middle of roll.
Clip through the roll from outside to center to make 7 petals, but don't separate petals.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Place teaspoonful of jam or pie filling in center of each roll after baking.
Vanilla glaze may be added; sprinkle with pecans.
Makes 10.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; lay in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, lemon juice, curry powder and mayonnaise until smooth.
Lay deboned chicken on broccoli; pour liquid over chicken.
Melt butter; stir in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fay's hot dog chili
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Rinse good.
Put in large kettle; add onion, 1/2 tomato juice.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add all remaining spices and tomato juice.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Red beans may be added for chili with beans.
Freezes well.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
In a mixer bowl, beat butter; add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, cornflakes, coconut and pecans.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool about 1 minute before removing to wire rack.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: g:
Layer onion and potatoes in a quart casserole dish. Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add garlic powder and pour over potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, covered.
Just before serving, sprinkle with parsley.

title: great pumpkin cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in morsels.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned. Makes 8 to 10 dozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add all dry ingredients and mix thoroughly at medium speed.
Then add carrots, nuts and raisins, mixing well.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch or 9-inch layer pans.
(Grease and flour pan.)
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Put butter frosting or whipped cream on top.

title: crunch salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower in small pieces.
Add green onions.
Then mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate for at least 3 hours for flavor to blend.
Serves 8.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook Prima Vera according to bag directions in salted water. Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Cut up vegetables.
Combine everything.
Make the night before and refrigerate.
Makes a large amount.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Whip Dream Whip with milk and vanilla according to package directions.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix with Dream Whip and pour into cooled graham cracker pie crust. Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.
Let cream filling cool prior to topping with blueberries.

title: dirt cake
directions: Using a blender or food processor, crush whole Oreo cookies to look like "dirt."

title: layered turkey salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a 2 1/2 quart bowl; set aside. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and white pepper; spread over salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Toss gently before serving, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pastor zesch's favorite sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat well in hot cooking oil; drain fat.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add water to keep meat moist until its tender.
Boil green peppers and carrots in small amount of water just until tender, drain and set aside.
Combine salt, sugar, soy sauce, vinegar and water; bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch paste.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add green peppers, carrots, pineapple and meat.
Cook one more minute.

title: frukt soppa
directions: Grind or chop fruit (except raisins).
Add 1 quart of water and 1 cinnamon stick to apples and cook until done.
Add 1 quart of water to other dried fruit and cook in large pot (at least 6 quart) until fruit is tender.
Add all ingredients and simmer until tapioca is clear.
Add sugar to sweeten to taste (1 to 2 cups).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine, mix with crumbs.
Divide into 3 parts.
Line bottom of a 2 1/2 quart dish with 1/3 of crumbs.
Layer 1/2 of chicken over crumbs. Mix mushroom soup with 1 cup of chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Layer another 1/3 of crumbs over soup and top with rest of chicken.
Mix chicken soup with 1 cup chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 400 for 30 minutes.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Beat eggs well, then add Karo and sugar.
Gradually beat in enough to mix well.
Add butter and nuts.
Put in uncooked crust. Bake at 350° for a few minutes.
Then turn oven down to 300° and cook slowly until firm.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix together and press in pie pan.
Freeze, then fill with vanilla ice cream and keep frozen until ready to eat.
Top with strawberries, peaches or any topping you like.

title: chocolate fudge pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 45
minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 9 1/2 x 13-inch casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook Tater Tots for 18 to 20 minutes, until hot.
Mix soup and milk together until smooth; pour over Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of soup and potato mixture.
Bake an additional 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and casserole is hot and bubbly.
Cool slightly; serve warm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
I usually cook my chicken breasts with garlic-pepper seasoning to give them more flavor.

title: mayonnaise substitute
directions: Combine cottage cheese in blender with wine vinegar, salt, pepper and seasonings, if desired, and a splash of nonfat milk. Cover and blend on high until graininess disappears and mixture is very smooth.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix together all ingredients until creamy and smooth.
Will frost 9 x 13-inch cake or double layer.

title: old fashioned soft custard
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Beat together slightly the eggs, sugar and salt.
Add to hot milk and mix well and return to top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring often, until eggs coat spoon.
Let cool and serve with whipped cream or cookies.

title: peanut patty
directions: Bring to boil and cook to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 stick oleo.
Beat until real thick and color changes.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet or pizza pan; spread to edges.
Cool and break into pieces.
May also be dropped by tablespoon onto greased sheets, but must be done quickly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and peel sweet potatoes.
Mash and add remaining ingredients.
Put into baking dish.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with tortillas.
Spoon browned hamburger over tortillas.
Pour beans over hamburger and pour Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom soup over hamburger.
Place Velveeta slices over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin banana bread
directions: This is a delicious bread that can be adapted many ways. Make it plain or mix in your favorite fruit. Give the starter and recipe as a gift during the holidays.

title: orange sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, salt, flour, juice and rind.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Bake in ungreased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
When removed from oven, invert pan on bottle to cool.

title: kugelis(grated potato casserole)
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Crisp it in frying pan.
Add grated onion to fat and saute.
Then add margarine and melt. Should make 1 cup fat all together.
Beat eggs slightly.
Leave grating of potatoes for last so they won't get too dark.
Grate potatoes and remove as much water as you can from them. They should be on the dry side.
Add the cup of fat with onion and bacon, slightly beaten eggs, salt and Carnation milk.
Mix it. Bake in a 400° preheated oven for 1/2 hour.
Reduce heat to 350°. Continue to bake for an hour or more. Should be nicely browned on top.

title: s'mores
directions: On paper plate or napkin, place graham cracker square.
Top with chocolate and marshmallow.
Microwave at High (10) for 15 to 20 seconds.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups of water for the cake.
Cream sugar and shortening; add hot raisins.
Sift flour, spices, salt and baking powder together.
Add flour and cold water and beat for 3 minutes.
Add soda dissolved in about 1/2 c. warm water from raisins.
Pour into oblong pan, greased and lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Scoop pulp out of tomatoes, leaving a thick shell; save pulp. Turn tomato shells upside down to drain.
Saute green pepper, green onions and celery until tender, but not brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in tomato pulp, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Put mixture into tomato shells.
Place in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch dish. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika and dot with butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.

title: country-fried pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops and mushrooms in shortening.
Pour off the fat.
Stir in soup, water and thyme.
Add onions and carrots. Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: low-salt, low-fat chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Mix sage, rosemary, oregano, garlic and pepper to make paste.
Rub chicken well with paste and place in bowl. Add oil and mix to coat.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Drain before cooking.
Saute chicken in nonstick pan about 10 minutes per side.
No additional oil will be needed.
Add wine and lemon juice to chicken and simmer a few minutes.
Serve chicken with the sauce spooned over the top.

title: italian sour cream cookies
directions: Beat margarine.
Add sugar and eggs.
Add anise flavoring and the remaining ingredients.
Drop big teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coq au vin(chicken in wine)
directions: In large skillet over medium flame, brown chicken breasts in butter and oil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Remove chicken.
To remaining fat in skillet, add flour.
Over low flame, cook, stirring about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and add gradually to flour mixture, stirring.
Over high flame, cook, stirring until sauce thickens.
Arrange chicken breasts in a glass 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Pour sauce over chicken; cover casserole with foil and bake in a preheated 350° gas oven 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve the chicken on a hot platter with the sauce poured over it.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pull apart cake
directions: Cut biscuits in four.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon in a bag. Add the biscuit quarters and shake until coated.
Layer in a Bundt pan the coated biscuits, then pecans.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with pecans.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Set aside one cup of cheese. Cook hamburger in stainless steel skillet and drain excess grease. Mix cooked hamburger, black pepper, salt, tomato sauce, white rice, onion, green pepper, chili powder and one cup of cheese together in a large 3-qt. casserole dish.

title: crabmeat cheese dip
directions: In double boiler, melt butter and Velveeta.
Add crab meat. Serve in chafing dish with crackers or Melba toast rounds.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and Italian dressing mix together. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill several hours or overnight.
The grated cheese can be sprinkled on top of salad instead of mixing it in with all other ingredients.

title: apricot chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine preserves, salad dressing and ginger. Set aside.
Place chicken in a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with apricot mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 50 to 55 minutes or until chicken juices run clear.
Yields 1 serving.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all of the above and chill.

title: cheese and eggs ole
directions: Beat eggs, then add all other ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly.
Cut into squares.
Serve with salsa.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt margarine with milk.
Add sugar in saucepan; add milk, margarine and salt.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add oats and cocoa.
Drop on wax paper.

title: gumbo jambalya
directions: Evenly combine all ingredients, except shrimp, in a 4-quart deep pan.
Cover with lid.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring often, until rice absorbs liquid.
During last 3 minutes of cooking, add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp turns pink.

title: cherry cheese squares
directions: Arrange 9 cracker halves in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch or 7 x 9-inch pan.
Cut to fit if needed.
Beat cheese until very soft. Add 1/2 cup milk gradually, blending smooth.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat well.
Fold in topping, reserving some for garnish.
Spread half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another cracker layer, then rest of pudding mixture.
Chill 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Top with cherry pie filling and garnish.

title: filled hamburgers
directions: Roll out or pat a giant patty of ground beef.
Fill with cheese and onion.
Fold patty in half, sealing edges.
Grill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and pepper in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Stir in beans and 2/3 c. onions.

title: marinade sauce
directions: Mix together and marinate steaks for 5 hours.
This is enough for 2 or 3 steaks.
Cook on grill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan (lightly greased or sprayed with Pam).
Drizzle butter or margarine over potatoes. Sprinkle salt, pepper and onions over potatoes.

title: lasagne
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add garlic, onion, beef and sausage, stirring frequently.
Cook 10 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Add prepared spaghetti sauce and parsley.
Bake to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 15 minutes.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Dice chicken. Cook broccoli and peas (separately until tender).
Combine chicken and noodles, then add vegetables.
Add chicken broth. Simmer a few minutes and serve.

title: ms. santa's zucchini bread
directions: Beat and mix well.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add milk and flour and beat on medium speed until mixture is light and creamy.
Add coconut.
Do not preheat oven!
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: golden punch
directions: In covered blender, use high speed to blend crushed pineapple with juice, one can at a time (30 seconds should be enough). Place in cold punch bowl the blended pineapple and juice, the undiluted lemonade concentrate and sugar.
Stir in club soda.
Add ice and serve.
Makes 10 cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add flour to mixture.
Set aside.
Beat together egg and milk.
In double boiler, melt chocolate until smooth.
After chocolate is melted, add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Top with whip cream when serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; rinse with cold water.
Put juice in small saucepan.
Add the eggs, sugar, flour and a dash of salt. Stir and bring to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Chill overnight, if possible.
(I've never chilled it overnight, and it tastes fine.) Add fruit and all of Cool Whip.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Sift
flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl. Add the
egg,
milk, butter, walnuts and cherries; beat well. Spoon into a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni-cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle cheese and pepperoni on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs, milk and basil until well blended.
Pour mixture into pie plate over cheese and pepperoni. Bake 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peaches and dream pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Whip the whipping cream, sugar and salt to soft peaks.
Stir in mayonnaise; mix well.
Fold in cranberry sauce and orange juice.
Line muffin tin with foil or paper liners.
Fill with cranberry mix.
Freeze until firm.
Put in Ziploc bag.
Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
May be used as salad or dessert.

title: liver pate
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and form into ball or log.
Garnish with parsley and sliced olives.
Good with bacon crackers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat soup and butter until melted.
Add cheese, sour cream and onion.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over grated potatoes; mix well. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and cocoa in mixing bowl. Put water, oil and margarine in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Pour in bowl with dry ingredients. Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into lightly greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (glass pan at 325°).

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix all ingredients together except beans and simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes uncovered.
Then add beans and cook additional 15 minutes.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix fruit with 1 cup of the sugar.
Melt butter in the dish you will bake the cobbler.
Blend remaining cup of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over the melted butter.
Do not stir! Put fruit on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The batter rises during baking.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla for 5 minutes. Add chocolate squares.
Mix well.
Add alternately to cream mixture 1 1/4 cup ice water and flour mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.
Use chocolate satin frosting.

title: split seconds
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend in butter, egg and vanilla.
Chill dough 1 hour.
(If you don't have time, skip chilling.)
Place dough on lightly floured board. Divide it into 4 parts.
Shape each into a 13 x 3/4-inch roll. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
With back of knife, make a 1/3-inch depression lengthwise down the center of each roll.
Fill with jelly.

title: butter herb fish
directions: Dip fillets into melted butter.
Combine remaining ingredients and coat the fillets.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water.
Stir to dissolve completely. Add crushed pineapple and ice cream.
Mix well and refrigerate. Stir once or twice before gelatin sets, so pineapple is mixed through. Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange slush
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Stir occasionally.
Freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and extract.
Add flour and baking powder, sifted.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: ham croissants
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie crust.
Prepare pie crust mix; roll to rectangle shape.
Cut into triangles.
Place a small portion of stuffing and roll (start at large end).
Heat oven to 400°.
Glue ends with water; glaze with egg yolk that has been diluted with water.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes on middle oven rack or until golden brown.
Yields 16 croissants.

title: sweet potato casserole 1
directions: Mash all ingredients together with an electric mixer and put in a greased casserole dish.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice; add fruit cocktail.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Let chill overnight.
Optional:
Top with 1 container of Cool Whip.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.

title: sweet potato candy
directions: Cream butter or margarine with vanilla.
Gradually add sugar and mix until thoroughly blended.
Add coconut and knead until smooth.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Shape like sweet potatoes or 2-inch sticks.
Allow to harden at room temperature for about 1 hour.
Roll in cinnamon or if preferred, roll in a combination of cinnamon and confectioners sugar.
Makes approximately 40 candies.

title: alaskan crab cakes
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in flour to make smooth mixture.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 minute.
Beat some of hot mixture into egg yolks; return to rest of mixture in saucepan.
Cook, stirring, several minutes, until thickened.
Remove from heat.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Place in a baking dish.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until tight.
Add eggs, cream and flavorings.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with bananas.
Use medium speed if mixing with an electric mixer.
Stir in pecans and pour in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar. Add 1 egg at a time, blending well. Add vanilla. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture; chill overnight. Drop by teaspoon into confectioners sugar and roll into balls. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes (DON'T OVERBAKE).

title: freezer slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Drain; add carrot and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Let cool and pour over slaw.
Put in freezer containers and freeze until ready to use.
This recipe may be made in larger quantities.

title: chicken curry
directions: Chop onions; saute in oil until soft.
Crush garlic; add to onions.
Chop or puree tomatoes; add to onions and garlic.
Add the salt, pepper and curry powder to the sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
You may need to add a little water to the sauce.
Pull all skin and fat from chicken.
Add chicken to sauce and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with pita bread, rice and salad sprinkled with lemon.

title: white chocolate raspberry-cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar, butter (melted) and cinnamon. Press into torte pan.
Cream the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and eggs, blending well.
Add melted white chocolate, cornstarch, whipping cream and vanilla.
Pour 1/3 mixture into crust.
Put a few berries on top.
Repeat twice.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter; pour into a baking dish.
Add oil, parsley, garlic, salt, cayenne and lemon juice.
Mix. Add shrimp. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer in a large skillet.
On medium heat, saute for 5 minutes.
Turn and saute on other side 5 minutes, or until shrimp is pink.
Remove from skillet; place on a platter and pour garlic mix over.

title: pumpkin flan cake
directions: In pan, melt granulated sugar, stirring until an even amber color.
Remove from heat and pour quickly into 9-inch pan.
Coat bottom and sides with the melted sugar.
Beat remaining ingredients except whipping cream until well blended.
Pour into glazed pie pan.
Place pie pan in pan of hot water (1/4 to 1/2-inch deep). Bake about 70 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Loosen sides of custard with a knife.
Invert cake on top of custard, then invert serving plate on top of cake.
Turn over all at once.
Decorate top of flan with whipped cream as you like.

title: polish sausage-kraut
directions: Saute in margarine, garlic and onion (do not brown; cook until tender).
Add water, bouillon, carrots, potatoes and caraway seed. Cook slowly until vegetables are tender.
Add sauerkraut and sausage; heat through.
Stir in sour cream mixture.
Heat and serve.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Combine water and dry yeast. Pour yeast mixture plus 4 cups self-rising flour into remaining ingredients. Stir well. Better if refrigerated overnight. Fill 1/2 in muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: church pineapple treat
directions: Mix pineapple and cheese.
Mix sugar, flour and juice. Combine the two mixtures and put into greased casserole, then put mixture of margarine and crumbs on top and bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: scallop cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower (which has been broken apart), until tender and arrange in greased casserole pan.
Then wash mushrooms and simmer 30 minutes.
Cut the mushrooms in slices; cook 3 minutes in 1 tablespoon fat, turning frequently.
Next melt 4 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add finely chopped onion; cook until tender. Add flour while stirring constantly.
When smooth add milk and mushroom liquid.
Add salt, paprika and mushroom slices and sprinkle with bread crumbs mixed with 2 tablespoons butter and paprika.
Bake in oven 30 minutes.

title: microwave san francisco chops
directions: Tip:
Rounder the shape of the dish, the better.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with rotary beater.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pastry-lined pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat
oven to 325°.
Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems. Saute caps
in
oil until coated with oil.
Drain.
Chop stems to make 1/2 cup.
Saute with onion and garlic.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Stir
in bread crumbs, parsley, cheese, egg, oregano and
salt and
pepper
to taste.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Dot with butter and bake for 30 minutes.

title: pear cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla. Mix well. Add pears and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.

title: shrimp and pasta salad(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; toss well. Combine yogurt and next 6 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Add to pasta mixture, tossing to coat.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with fresh dill weed, if desired.
Yield:
6 servings (serving size:
1 cup).
Calories:
224; fat grams:

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Over medium heat, bring sugar and Karo to light boil. Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together and bake.
Bake until hot through.

title: kitchen sink cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients in order. Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: poor man pie
directions: In medium size bowl, mix flour, milk and sugar.
Cut stick of butter into 1/4-inch pats and layer on bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour batter over butter.
Pour pie filling in middle of batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: orange glazed yams
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and slice.
Place in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; heat in a saucepan until boiling.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In mixing bowl put confectioners sugar.
Make a hole in the center of it.
Put margarine, milk, peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs in the hole.
Work up well.
(Add more milk if necessary.)
Form into balls and dip into icing.
(You can double the mixture and still have enough icing without doubling the icing.)

title: swalsies 269 punch
directions: Freeze whole lemons, limes and oranges to act as ice.
Looks pretty and does not water down punch.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mixes well with any champagne, liquor, etc.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix according to directions.
Cool completely.
Beat milk and pudding; add slowly to whipped cream cheese and put on cake.
Add drained pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Top with coconut.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
May be frozen before baking.
Freeze on cookie sheet first, then transfer to plastic bags for freezer storage.
Thaw before baking.

title: bernice heugatter's cucumber mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Refrigerate until it begins to set, then stir in cucumbers, celery, onions, sour cream and cottage cheese.
Pour into 1-quart mold and refrigerate until set.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: In a pot, boil 1 cup water.
Add lima beans and carrots; cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Drain; reserve 1/3 cup liquid.

title: florida cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients, then mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Remove from oven and put icing on immediately while warm.

title: the best salad dressing!
directions: Mix oil, mustard, sugar and tomato soup.
Add vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic.
Mix.
Let set overnight in fridge.
It's wonderful.

title: halibut with artichokes
directions: Melt margarine; stir in flour.
Add milk, wine, hot sauce and cheese.
Heat sauce until cheese melts; pour over fish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Bake uncovered.

title: hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape.
Grill or broil.
May also be frozen with sheets of waxed paper between.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a big bowl, adding any or all of the last ingredients.
Mix all and bake in muffin tins at 350°.

title: barbecue rib sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil, add everything else.
Simmer for a while. Best made a day or so ahead of time.
Brush on meat just before removing from charcoal, oven or microwave to avoid scorching. Makes about 2 cups.
Adjust ingredients to taste.

title: mamie eisenhower fudge
directions: Butter sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine the sugar, salt and milk.
Heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to rolling boil and boil for about 8 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add the chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Beat until chocolate is melted. Add the Marshmallow Creme, beating until all is well blended. Add nuts.
Turn into a shallow 10 x 12-inch buttered pan and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: cheesy garden casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook broccoli, carrots, zucchini and green beans in boiling water until tender.
Spoon vegetables over rice.
Top with marinara sauce. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine cheese; sprinkle over casserole.
Return to oven to melt cheese for about 5 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan. Sprinkle brown sugar in melted butter. Layer peaches on top of brown sugar. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk; pour over peaches. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces and roll in flour. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a skillet, brown meat on both sides in oil.
Top with onions, celery and carrots.
In a medium bowl, combine tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Spoon over veggies.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 - 2 hours.

title: caramel nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with sour milk.
Heat sweet milk; add a little at a time, then add vanilla and nut meats.
Bake at 400° until done. Frost with caramel icing.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: apple slices
directions: *More if using softer apples that cook down more.

title: gram's salad delight
directions: Boil crushed pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes. Mix in jello powder and cool. Beat together chilled milk and cream cheese, whipping until stiff.

title: south carolina ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients except ribs in medium sized mixing bowl.
Place ribs in large 17 x 12 x 2 1/2-inch Redi-Pan roasting pan; pour sauce over ribs.
Cover with heavy-duty Reynolds wrap or other aluminum foil and marinate in refrigerator 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake, covered, 55 minutes.
Remove foil; turn ribs over.
Bake, uncovered, 55 minutes, basting every 15 minutes.
To serve, cut into 2 or 3 rib sections.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey-tomato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until soften.
Add the bay leaf, thyme stock, tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add turkey and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and serve garnished with additional minced thyme if desired and serve.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Wash chicken in cold water and place in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 20 minutes uncovered.
Cover and bake 30 minutes more or until chicken is done.

title: chicken tostado casserole
directions: Crush tostados in bottom of casserole dish.
Boil, debone and cut chicken into bite-size pieces and layer on top of tostado chips.
Mix cream of mushroom and Ro-Tel tomatoes and pour over chicken.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Delicious served over rice or noodles.

title: stir-n-roll two crust pie
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Pour oil and milk into measuring cup but do not stir.
Pour all at once into flour mixture and stir lightly until just mixed.
Roll 1/2 between waxed paper.
If paper begins to wrinkle, turn over and roll the other side.
Peel off top paper and turn into pan and peel off other paper.

title: beef eggplant bake
directions: Cut beef cubes in 1/2-inch strips across the grain.
Combine flour, 2 teaspoons salt and pepper. Dredge meat and brown in hot fat in large frying pan, 1/3 at a time.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Break tomatoes into pieces and set aside.
Add reserved tomato liquid, water, onions and dill seed.
Cover and cook slowly 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices.
Pare and place in large saucepan with boiling water and salt.
Boil 5 to 10 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove to absorbent paper and pat dry. Combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle half the crumb mixture in bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Place eggplant in layers in casserole and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Add meat mixture and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake in moderate 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until eggplant is done. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Sprinkle wing pieces with salt and pepper.
Cook in hot oil for
minutes or until golden brown.
Drain well.
Melt butter and add
hot sauce to taste; add vinegar.
Put wings on platter and pour butter mixture over them.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes, or until done.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; mix all the ingredients together.
Place in greased bowl in refrigerator for at least 7 hours (can make up dough the night before).
Make rolls out 1 1/2 or 2 hours before serving time.
Cook at 400°.
Makes about 2 dozen rolls.
Dough will keep in the refrigerator a week or so.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Bake cornbread according to package directions.
Set aside. Cook eggplant and mash.
Add crumbled cornbread and milk to mashed eggplant.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper.
Add cream of chicken soup and poultry seasoning.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Fifteen minutes before you take it out of oven, add cheese (grated) to top of casserole, enough to cover.

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Bring to a full rolling boil and continue to boil for 5 minutes:
white sugar and milk.
Crush the crackers; chop the nuts.
As soon as you take the sugar mixture off the stove, add the crackers, vanilla, peanut butter and nuts and stir until it starts to thicken.
Then put into a buttered pan.
Cut when cool.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Grind wafers.
Set 1 cup aside for topping.
Heat 1 stick margarine.
Mix 2 cups wafer crumbs.
Press in oblong dish.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar together.
Add 1/2 to crust.
Add can of pie filling.
Then add the other half.
Sprinkle 1 cup crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours. Serve on bed of lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in butter.
Drain liquid from one can of peas.
Mix peas, liquid, sauteed vegetables, soup, water chestnuts and pimiento.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients together, then add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey cookies
directions: Mix and drop onto greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until light brown.
For a ginger cookie, add 1 teaspoon ginger instead of the vanilla.

title: bacon and cheese cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Stir in milk and oil.
Gradually add boiling water, stirring until batter is a thick pouring consistency, not runny.
Pour into greased and heated cast-iron skillets or muffin pans and bake until deep gold in color.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in 4 cups water until meat comes off bones easily. In another pan, boil together 1/2 cup rice, onion and boiling water.
When rice is done, put it in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chicken pieces.
Take the chicken broth and make a gravy with flour, yolks and salt.
Pour gravy over meat and top with bread crumbs browned in butter.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1/2 hour.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and add mayonnaise and cold water.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: spice apple cake
directions: Pare and slice apples; put sugar and cinnamon on apples and mix, then let stand.
Mix eggs, sugar, baking powder, vanilla, oil and flour.
Add apple mix by hand.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot spinach artichoke dip
directions: In a large nonstick skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray, cook and stir onion until tender. Add spinach; cook and stir over medium heat until heated through. Reduce heat to low; stir in cream cheese and sour cream. Add the artichoke hearts, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and red pepper flakes. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through. Transfer to an ungreased 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Cover and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve warm with Melba toast or pita chips. Yield: 18 servings.

title: aztec pie
directions: Brown meat; add onion.
Combine ingredients except 1/2 of cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: grandma libby's squash souffle
directions: Steam or boil zucchini until tender; chop squash well.
Add butter to frying pan and saute onion until it turns clear.
Add onion to squash; mix well.
Mix in beaten egg, sugar, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Stir in crumbled crackers and mix well.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cottage pie
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together.
Drain off grease.
Put into baking dish or casserole.
Put corn on top of hamburger.
Top off with potatoes.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put pad of butter on top, if desired, for browning.

title: macaroni and pork chops
directions: Flour and brown pork chops.
Mix together tomato sauce and soup.
Add spices to taste.
Reserve 1/2 cup mix for topping.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Mix and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients until very thick.
Shake well before using.
This is delicious served over a fruit salad of grapefruit sections and kiwi.

title: lemon poppy seed pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl combine all cake ingredients.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until all ingredients are moistened.
Beat at high speed, scraping bowl often, until smooth (1 - 2 minutes).
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan or 10 inch tube pan.
Bake for 55 - 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: orange crush pound cake
directions: Thoroughly cream together vegetable shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add orange drink alternately with sifted flour.
Add flavorings. Put into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool before icing.
Top with icing.

title: black and white cheesecake bites
directions: Crust:
In medium saucepan over very low heat, melt chocolate chips and butter, stirring until smooth.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Remove 1/4 cup mixture for later use.
Press remaining graham cracker mixture evenly in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: cream puff dough
directions: Mix the milk, butter and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add the flour all at once, stirring well with wooden spatula.
Cook the dough for 2 or 3 minutes on medium heat to dry out and then place in cold bowl.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Select a pan large enough to hold the chicken without overlapping.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix the flour, mustard, paprika, pepper and salt in a paper bag.
Shake the chicken pieces in it one at a time.
Lay the floured chicken in the pan; turn in the butter once.
Dot with small pieces of butter.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes for small chickens or 45 minutes for large.
Turn once during this time.
Turn the oven to a very hot 450° and bake 10 to 15 minutes more, until chicken is brown and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beau catcher's chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, paprika, thyme and onion powder.
Dip chicken in buttermilk and then into dry ingredients, coating well. Pour butter into baking dish, place chicken in butter and turn to coat.
Place chicken, skin side down, in a single layer.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake for another 30 minutes or until tender.

title: stephen putnam's root vegetable gratin
directions: Place a medium saucepan over medium heat and add oil.
When oil is hot, add onions and sweat them until translucent.
Add cream, chicken stock and herbs.
Bring mixture to a simmer, then turn off heat and set mixture aside.
Slice the root vegetables thin and place them in alternating fashion in a casserole dish, filling dish just 3/4 full.
Strain cream mixture through a fine sieve and pour it over the vegetables in the casserole.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until vegetables are soft and tender.
Remove foil from top of casserole and bake for 15 minutes, until bread crumbs are golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together egg, buttermilk or sour milk, onion and water; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add egg mixture to cornmeal mixture; stir just until moistened.

title: fantastic dessert
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar, flour and nuts.
Mix, then press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° or until light brown.

title: chinese noodle chocolate candy
directions: Melt chips; add noodles and nuts.
Add a little paraffin. Stir to blend.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Stir in water and cook 15 minutes.
Add butter.
Pour over sweet potatoes in a flat pan, so each piece is covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ant killer
directions: Dash equals 2 to 4 drops.

title: hot garlic pickle
directions: Place a small piece of garlic and 2 pods hot pepper and small head
of
dill
in
clean
jars.
Bring water, salt and vinegar to a boil; add sliced or small whole cucumbers to jars and
pour boiling
mixture over this.
Add a pinch of alum to each
jar
and seal.
Let
stand
for 2 weeks.
Makes about 5 quarts of pickles.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time and mix thoroughly.
Gradually add flour, baking powder and then the fruit and orange rind.
Nuts may be added to the mixture or sprinkled in bottom of pan before adding the batter.
The cake is baked in a special grooved pan which is about 4 inches across and 11 inches long and resembles a tube which has been cut lengthwise.
Grease and flour pan and add batter.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool a few minutes and then turn pan upside-down on a wire rack to cool completely.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Coat well with Italian dressing or one of your choice.

title: pan gravy for roast poultry
directions: Remove roast poultry to a serving platter; keep warm.
Leaving crusty bits in the roasting pan, pour pan drippings into a large measuring cup.
Skim off and reserve fat from the pan drippings. (To skim the fat from the drippings, tilt the measuring cup and spoon off the oily liquid that rises to the top.)

title: habitant pea soup
directions: Pick over peas and soak overnight or according to package directions.
Boil for 10 minutes in water to cover.
Drain; discard water.
Place peas in deep kettle.
Add cold water, salt pork, vegetables, salt and pepper to taste and allspice.
Simmer, covered, over lowest possible heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cracklin' cornbread
directions: *City folks can use crumbled, crisp bacon.

title: reese's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter and butter.
Then add powdered sugar; mix well!
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler with paraffin wax.
Dip balls into chocolate and lay on wax paper.

title: fruit-filled pockets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel pear.
Slice in half and remove the core; dice.
Melt butter in saucepan until half melted.
Place 2 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt in bowl and mix together. Add milk and butter and stir until completely mixed.
Sprinkle about 1/4 cup flour on kitchen surface.
Place dough on floured surface and knead about 5 times.
Gently even it out with your hands and then roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut circles out of dough with cookie cutter.
Cut as many as you can.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
In a mixing bowl, add egg and water and stir with fork until blended.
Dip finger into egg and then dab it around the edge of each circle.
Spoon a generous amount (1 teaspoon) of marmalade or jam in the center of each circle and about 2 to 3 pieces of pear chunks on top of the marmalade.
Fold each circle in half, using a fork to press the edges together.
Bake in oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
This recipe makes 10 filled biscuits.
Let cool 10 minutes and enjoy.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut individual biscuits into 4 pieces.
Put 2/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon into bag.
Shake the biscuit pieces in this mixture and place into greased Bundt pan.
Melt together the 1 1/2 sticks butter, 1 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and turn over onto serving plate.

title: okra pilau
directions: Saute bacon until crisp and set aside.
Add the boiling water to the bacon drippings.
Add okra and tomatoes; let come to a brisk boil.
Add rice, salt, pepper and basil.
Cover and cook over low heat about 30 minutes or until rice is tender and fluffy. Add more water during cooking, if needed.
When ready to serve, garnish with the bacon crumbled on top.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix and melted margarine and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Warm soups and milk together.
Mix chicken with peas, onions, water chestnuts and almonds.
Mix 2 mixtures together. Pour over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: your choice meat loaf
directions: Blend well all ingredients and shape into loaf. Pat well to cover air pockets. Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Drain off grease and garnish with ketchup or tomato sauce and thinly sliced green pepper rings.

title: golden raisin bread
directions: Combine raisins, shortening and 1 1/4 cups water.
Heat to boiling, stirring until shortening melts.
Cool to lukewarm. Soften yeast in remaining 1/2 cup water.
Add sugar, salt, spices and 1 cup flour.
Mix well.
Add raisin mixture.
Gradually add remainder of flour.
Knead 3 minutes.
Brush dough with oil. Cover; let rise in bowl until double, about 1 3/4 hours.
Punch down.
Shape into 2 medium loaves.
Brush top with oil.
Let rise until double (45 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Boil venison on high until foam comes to the top of kettle. Skim off foam and boil on medium-low for almost 1 hour.
Drain and rinse lightly.
Cut up and fry in butter flavored Crisco and onion.
Stir in mushrooms, steak sauce (undiluted) and Worcestershire sauce.
Season with Mrs.
Dash no salt.
Stir in stroganoff mix.
Mix it according to directions on packet.
Add sour cream.
Simmer until heated through.
Add cooked noodles.

title: eleanor's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon in 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Lay bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bible honey cake
directions: Bake in moderate oven (350°) in tube pan for 50 minutes.

title: shrimp pie
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine until tender.
Combine cooked vegetables with all other ingredients, except shrimp.
Cook until the soup is smooth.
Add shrimp; cook until hot.
Pour into pie shell; top with second pie shell.
Seal off edges; make slits in top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Remove from heat; let stand 20 minutes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla, dates and nuts in a large skillet until it leaves the sides of the skillet.
Pour into a bowl that has Rice Krispies and mix well.
Separate into 3 or 4 balls and roll in coconut.
Cool and slice as needed.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time) and the remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pickle
directions: Pour liquid off pickles and slice.
Add sugar, raisins, celery seed and mustard seed.
Let stand 3 days.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and then add pecans.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell (9-inch) or 26 ounce pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turkey and potato pie
directions: Make mashed potatoes.
In skillet, brown turkey with onion. Mix in soup.
Spread turkey mixture in a glass baking dish. Spread mashed potatoes on top of turkey.
Cook in oven or microwave until heated through.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2 x 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Place apple slices in the pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: diabetic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into loaf.
Place in a lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: In water boil 1 cup rice until it begins to absorb the water, then add 1 cup milk.
Continue to cook on low flame now.
Add 1 cup sugar and continue to boil on low flame, stirring constantly.
Add 1 cup milk more.
Continue to absorb liquids.
Add 1 can of evaporated milk and mix in it 1 egg yolk.
Continue to boil until rice is cooked.
Add almond extract and nutmeg.
Cool in refrigerator.
You can pour into Pyrex or in other container to serve.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon (1/2 teaspoon).

title: mountain breakfast deep dish
directions: Crumble, fry and drain sausage.
Scramble 1 dozen eggs, using salt, pepper and milk.
Add grated Cheddar cheese and cream of mushroom soup to egg mixture.
Place sausage in bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Add egg mixture and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Allow to set a few minutes before serving with hot biscuits.

title: fennel seed cookies
directions: Combine butter, fennel seed and salt.
Add sugar, then egg. Sift together flour and baking powder and add to sugar mixture. Chill the dough at least 2 hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone.
Line casserole dish with chicken.
Mix chicken broth, chicken soup and 1/2 can water and pour over chicken.
If you want to add vegetables, add Veg-All or you can use frozen vegetables to mixture before you pour it over chicken.
Mix oleo, self-rising flour and sweet milk.
This will be soupy.
Spoon over pie.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: crustless ricotta pie
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch pie plate.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into prepared pie plate.
Bake at 350° until nice and brown.
Chill in refrigerator.
Yummy!

title: caramel ice cream
directions: Make a syrup of brown sugar and water.
Cook 5 minutes and cool.
Mix cornstarch and egg yolks and cook until it coats a wooden spoon.
Mix with syrup and strain.
Add cream, beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Add milk to the fill line on a gallon freezer.
Freeze until firm.

title: danish puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour quickly and stir hard.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well. Add flavoring.
Blend well and spread on two strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, frost.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and place in buttered casserole.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze in freezer until very mushy.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.
This makes at least 6 gallons of punch and can be made in smaller batches as needed.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Measure and sift together 3 times the flour, 3/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar and cocoa.
Set aside in sifter.
Measure in large mixing bowl the egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed until foamy.
Slowly (1 tablespoon at a time) add 3/4 cup sifted granulated sugar, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating at highest speed after last addition until meringue holds stiff peaks.
Sift cocoa mixture, 1/4 cup at a time, over meringue, folding gently with wire whip or rubber spatula (not mixer).
Repeat sifting and mixing until all cocoa mixture is folded in.
Gently push batter into ungreased tube pan (preferably one with a removable bottom).
Cut through batter to break up large air bubbles.
Be sure batter is level and touches the sides of the pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then top with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
minutes.
Grease a Bundt pan. Spread 10
nuts
on
bottom of pan.
Decorate with maraschino cherries on top of nuts.
Pour batter in pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: coconut and pecan pie
directions: Whip eggs and add sugar, milk and other ingredients.
Put in pie shell and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove foil and bake for 15 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 15 minutes.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in
large
bowl and mix well. Spoon into jars and
seal.
To serve, add 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.
Makes about 40 cups.

title: strawberry shake
directions: In French drip coffeepot or percolator, use one heaping tablespoon of Cafe du Monde coffee and chicory for each cup of boiling water.
Add one extra spoon of coffee for the pot.
Mix freshly brewed coffee with equal amounts of hot homogenized milk or to suit taste.

title: 1 dish meal in a pie
directions: Brown flour in oleo.
Add beef broth and hot sauce.
Add Veg-All, beef and salt; mix well.
Pour meat mixture into crust. Mix together cheese, milk and eggs.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, until cheese mixture is browned.
Serves 4.

title: night before casserole
directions: A great way to free up the day for quilting.

title: mama's best bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables and combine first 8 ingredients.
Combine sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour over vegetables, tossing well.
Cover and chill.

title: turkey tenderloin with fruit sauce
directions: Preheat broiler and line with foil.
In medium bowl, toss turkey tenderloins; toss with lemon juice.
Broil (4 inches from heat) for 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn.
Broil 3 or 4 minutes more to golden brown.
Remove, saving juices.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Add cubed bread and mix well.
Beat eggs until light.
Add flour, sugar, salt and pineapple to eggs. Mix.
Pour into casserole and mix with butter and bread.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until like custard or when knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: shish-ka-bob
directions: Mix liquids and spices.
(Red wine works best for beef and lemon juice works best for chicken and lamb.)
Mix in chunked onion and green pepper.
Marinate meat and vegetables for 24 hours in refrigerator for best flavor.
Place meat and vegetables on skewers and grill.
Serve over rice.

title: country chicken soup("crock-pot recipe")
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot, except noodles, in order listed.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 4 to 6 hours). One hour before serving, remove chicken and cool slightly.
Remove meat from bones and return to crock-pot.
Add noodles.
Turn to high.
Cover and cook 1 hour.

title: nonalcoholic holiday punch
directions: In a 3 quart saucepan, combine sugar, water, spices and salt. Bring
to
boil.
Add
fruit juices.
Serve hot.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cook onions, tomatoes and chili powder.
Simmer until thick. Add cheese and cayenne pepper.
Serve over toast.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter; remove from heat.
Stir in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Stir dry ingredients and walnuts into sugar mixture.
Spread in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.
Makes 48 bars.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan and bake until light golden brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together and spread on cooled crust.
Decorate with rows of strawberries and kiwi, then bananas or other fruits that are in season.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Cut into slices. The cookie dough can be found in the dairy case.

title: seasoned seeds
directions: Remove membrane from seeds.
If seeds are washed, pat dry. Place in a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Add remaining ingredients. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly toasted, stirring 4 to 5 times.
Cooking time will depend on size of seeds and moistness.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt, water, juice and melted butter.
Separate eggs; beat egg yolks and add to sugar mixture. Beat egg whites stiff, then add egg mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: easy chicken breast
directions: Cut chicken breasts into halves.
Sprinkle salt and pepper onto chicken pieces, let stand for five minutes.
Dip chicken in olive oil.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oven-baked chicken
directions: You will also need a 6 pound Purdue oven stuffer roaster.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thicken pineapple juice with the cornstarch over medium heat. Mix cornstarch with a little water before adding to juice so it won't lump.
You may add 1 package of sugar substitute to sauce when cool, if desired.
Pour over fruit and stir.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage-cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 5 minutes or until brown.

title: tandy cakes
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour.
Scald milk.
Add margarine to milk.
Add to flour mixture.
Bake on a large greased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread with peanut butter.
Chill.
Melt Hershey bars; spread on top.
Chill; cut at room temperature.

title: bride's pink punch(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Dissolve drink mix in cold water; add sugar and stir well. Add pineapple juice and dissolved gelatin. Refrigerate. Add carbonated beverage and sherbet just before serving. Serves about 30.

title: nutti fingers
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add flour.
Add vanilla and nuts (finely chopped).
Shape into thin finger shapes.
Bake on cookie sheet in 275° oven approximately 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: cranberry surprise pie
directions: Grease well 8-inch pie plate.
Spread cranberries on bottom of plate.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and nuts.
Beat egg well; add 1/2 cup sugar gradually and beat until mixed.
Add flour, melted butter and shortening to egg and sugar mixture; beat well.
Pour batter over top of cranberries.
Bake in slow oven, 325° for 45 minutes until crust is brown.
Cut like pie.
Serve warm or cold with scoops vanilla ice cream.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place 8 slices of bread flat in 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
On each slice, top with 1 slice ham, 1 slice cheese and remaining 8 slices of bread.
Mix eggs, beaten with salt, pepper, mustard, onion, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Pour mixture over the top of bread.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Note:
Use a 12 cup round tube pan.

title: microwaved mullet fillets
directions: Spray glass pie plan with Pam.
Arrange fillets around pan with thicker end toward outside.
Sprinkle fillets with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, turning half way through cooking time.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken using only half of sauce.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Cook 1/2 bag of noodles. Mix with rest of sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Cook 1/2 hour longer. Bake at 350°.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients as pie dough.
Add milk and egg. Spread in 9-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken and pick off bone.
Put celery, onions, carrots and noodles into pan and cover with water and boil.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° about an hour or until firm in center.

title: greek lasagna (pasticho)
directions: Add salt and pepper to ground beef.
Fry until juices are absorbed.
Add chopped onion, parsley and 4 tablespoons of butter; brown well.
Add tomato sauce and water and simmer until liquid is absorbed, about 15 minutes.

title: almond roca
directions: Cook butter, sugar and water in heavy saucepan to 250°. Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 of the almonds. Spread out on buttered cookie sheet.
Mix chocolate chips and remaining almonds and sprinkle over hot candy.
Press into candy.
Let cool. Break into pieces.
(I freeze the candy and take out a little bit every once in awhile.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Add additional mayo before serving, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: southern corn pone
directions: Mix the ingredients together and add cold water until a soft dough is formed.
Mold into oval cakes with the hands and put into a well greased pan.
Bake at 425° until the crust is brown.
Eat while it is hot.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook the noodles according to package directions and drain well.
Place noodles in hot casserole or deep platter over low heat.
Mix the butter, cheese and cream together.
Add (a little at a time) the butter mixture to the noodles, tossing gently after each addition.
Season with freshly ground black pepper to taste. Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple. Mix all ingredients together well. Chill.

title: dump cake
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, pour all of fruit (juice included) into bottom.
Sprinkle cake mix directly out of box onto top of fruit. Cut pats of butter and spread evenly over top of cake mix.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven or until top is golden brown.

title: no bake date cookies
directions: On medium heat, combine sugar, butter or margarine and dates and cook for 8 minutes.
Sit off and cool, then add vanilla.
Fold in Rice Krispies and shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: brownies
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco, cocoa, water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Set off and let cool.
Mix flour, soda, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix oleo, soups and rice together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Lay chicken breasts on top.
Brush chicken with melted oleo and sprinkle with some paprika.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: homemade hot chocolate mix
directions: If you would like a real chocolately flavor add 1/3 cup-1/2 cup Hershey's European Dutch processed cocoa. Stir all together, store in airtight container.
To make hot cocoa, mix 4 heaping tablespoons with 8 oz. boiling water.
Add miniature marshmallows, whipping cream or cinnamon stick for flavor.
Try using different flavor of powdered creamers for different flavors.

title: french fried eggplant
directions: Clean and cut eggplant.
Peel and cut into French fry strips. Soak in a water and salt solution for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Drain on paper toweling.
Shake strips in a flour, salt and pepper mixture. Deep fat fry for 3 to 5 minutes at 325°.
Remove from fat; drain on paper toweling.
Serve hot with lemon and salt.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Have meats ground together twice.
Soak bread in cream 5 minutes.
Soak onions in 1 tablespoon water.
Combine meats, crumb mixture, onion, parsley and seasonings.
Beat fluffy (about 5 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer, plus 8 minutes by hand).
Form in 1-inch balls (for easier shaping, wet hands when necessary).
Brown only a few at a time in 2 tablespoons butter.

title: cuban empanadas
directions: Fry beef or chicken in very hot pan.
Mix picante sauce, corn, cheese and sugar together in a bowl.
Flatten biscuits.
Beat egg and brush around edge of biscuits.
Add meat to other ingredients; mix.
Spoon mixture in the middle of biscuit.
Fold over and press edges together with fork.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: easy orange sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into freezer can.
Freeze.

title: apple toss
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add sour cream, wine, and mayonnaise together and spread over the first 5 ingredients.
Top with almonds or walnuts

title: skip's granny cake
directions: Mix together and let come to a boil, then boil 5 minutes. When done, add 1 teaspoon vanilla to the glaze mixture.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in 1/4-inch strips.
Brown in hot shortening.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is crisp-tender.
Combine remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Add to meat.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve over noodles.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown onion in oleo.
Add beef and brown.
Add salt and pepper.
Cut up cabbage in 1-inch squares.
Add to ground beef mixture.
Cover and cook slow about 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and cheese and mix thoroughly.
Put in greased casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Good reheated next day.

title: kenny's favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: In large stock pot, saute onions, celery, carrot and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Add parsley, crushed red pepper flakes, oregano, rosemary, basil, cloves and black pepper.
Mix enough to blend the herbs with the vegetable mixture and the strained tomatoes and Romano cheese.
Bring to a gentle boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, partially covered.
Store in plastic or glass container, never aluminum.

title: b.j.'s broccoli casserole
directions: Combine and blend together the broccoli, onion, mushroom soup, mayonnaise, egg and salt and pepper. Put all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Add crumbled cheese crackers on top and
layer 1/2 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese on crumbled cheese crackers.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, egg and pecans together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together cream cheese, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let set 24 hours before cutting.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain.
Place in casserole.
Pour cream of chicken soup over meat.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: never fail kraut
directions: Mix salt and vinegar.
Mix with water.
Put kraut in jars and pour mixture over it.
Seal.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Fold in chips.
Bake in bundt pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: golden coins(carrot relish)
directions: Slice and cook the carrots.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate for 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: spaghetti meat sauce and meat balls
directions: Brown meat in skillet and
drain; put aside.
In large pot, put tomato sauce, paste and water and bring to boil, then add meat and all other ingredients and simmer 2 or 3 hours to desired thickness, stirring occasionally.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water in a large saucepan just until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, peel and slice into a large bowl. Cover.
Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Pour off drippings; measure 1/4 cup and return to skillet.
Saute onion in drippings until soft.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar and water. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Pour over potatoes. Toss lightly to coat.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top.
Serve warm.

title: marinated olives
directions: Mix all together, then marinate 2 to 4 hours and serve.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch oval and then slice each oval lengthwise into matchstick.
Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable oil.

title: nonnie's zucchini and sausage pasta
directions: Heat olive oil and garlic; do not brown!
Add sausage, remove when cooked.
To pan juices, add onion, celery and carrots.
Saute until softened (not mushy).
Put aside with sausage.
Saute cubed zucchini (first wash with vegetable brush, but do not skin). Zucchini should be crisp.
Add ingredients from bowl.
Add
cream, wine or vermouth (to taste, about 3 tablespoons), tomato paste (about 1 tablespoon) and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooked pasta and cheese to taste.

title: spinach-cheese savory
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except spinach. Pour into buttered casserole dish with lid.
Take a box of frozen chopped spinach; carve little chunks off and let fall on top of the cheese/egg mixture.
Bake one hour.
Let sit for 5 minutes before eating.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix
lime
with
water
and pour over cucumbers and let stand for
hours.
Rinse well, about 5 times.
Cover with clear water
and let stand for 4 hours.
Heat vinegar, sugar, celery seed,
pickling spice and salt to lukewarm.
Pour over cucumbers. Let
stand
overnight.
Take
pickles
and vinegar solution
and boil
for 20 minutes.
Add green food coloring. Put in jars and seal.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Cook rice, drain and mix with remaining ingredients.
Top with toasted almonds.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half and take out seeds, then wash.

Mix the ground beef, cooked rice, onion, salt, pepper, tomato soup and Worcestershire sauce. Fill green peppers with mixture and put in electric skillet. Fill the center of skillet with the carrots. Pour in the water, then place cover on skillet.
Turn current to high. When steam escapes from vent, turn switch to lowest position and cook about 40 minutes until carrots are tender.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken. Remove skin and bones.
Dice chicken.
Cook 1 (12 oz.) pkg. egg noodles in chicken broth.
Combine:
Chopped chicken, drained noodles and all other ingredients (except cracker crumbs and butter) and place in large casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: san diego fudge
directions: Melt marshmallows with oleo.
Boil milk with sugar for 6 minutes.
Combine the 2 mixtures and pour over chocolate chips. Mix well until creamy.
Add vanilla and nutmeats.
Pour into buttered pan and chill.
(Cannot fail.)

title: spiced nuts
directions: In a deep heavy skillet, melt the butter and stir in the nuts. Cook the nuts over low heat, stirring frequently for about 20 minutes or until nuts are heated through and lightly browned.

title: dirt cake
directions: Save 1 Oreo cookie.
Crush remaining cookies in blender or food processor.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and condensed milk.
Add pudding mix and milk; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a 12-inch clay flower pot, put one Oreo cookie over hole and start layering with crushed cookies on top.
Optional:
Stick silk flower out of dirt.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix like biscuit dough and roll out thin.
Cut into 2-inch squares and drop into hot oil; baste with spatula until golden. Drain on paper towels.
Pinch corner off of sopaipilla and fill with honey.
Enjoy!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: orange cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon in a
plastic bag and shake biscuit pieces to coat. Place biscuits in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and mix with sugars and cinnamon.
Add nuts and pour over top of biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Turn coffee cake out and top with glaze.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Shape hamburg into meatballs while onions and peppers are sauteing in oil and black pepper.
When onions are clear, add meatballs and cook until done. Place rest of ingredients in 4-quart pan. Add meatballs when done.
Simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Cook sausage, onion, peppers and mushrooms; drain well.
Cool completely.
Thaw dough; let rise.
Roll out thin.
